I was playing ice hockey on April 10, 2021 when I started to experience shortness of breath.  Coming to the bench between shifts is part of the game and that time on the bench is used to recover (both for your muscles and for your cardiovascular system).  However, towards the latter part of the game, I continued to be short of breath even while sitting on the bench.  Then in the last 10 minutes or so of the game, I fell to the ice for no reason.  It was as if my muscles had just totally failed.  I thought the shortness of breath may have been a sign of a Covid infection since I had not reached the 14 day period after my second shot.  So I went to urgent care to get a Covid test.  My test came back negative, but the doctor was concerned with my symptoms, so he took an x-ray of my heart and an ECG.  He said that he noticed a blur around my heart, but didn't have any explanation.  He thought I was in very good health, so he gave me a list of heart specialists to contact if I had another 'episode'.  Fortunately, I did not have another episode.  The only reason that I am submitting this incident is because I understand the administration is having an emergency meeting to review cases of an inflamed heart.  I am not sure my situation was an inflamed, but I wanted to have my episode documented in case my situation was a temporary adverse reaction to the vaccine.

I was 36 weeks and 5 days pregnant at the time I received my 2nd dose of the Moderna vaccination. This is my 2nd pregnancy, both low risk, and my due date is June 21. I have been monitoring my blood glucose regularly as I failed the glucose tolerance test but have had no problems with high blood glucose levels and do not have gestational diabetes. My normal BP during this pregnancy has been in the 90-100/50's-60's range. I got my 2nd vaccine on May 29 around 9:15 am, by 9:21 I suddenly got a strong feeling as if I was about to vomit, then my heart began to pound and was racing, then I felt dizzy and light headed, then my mouth went extremely dry. I told the people at the pharmacy that I was ill and they had me sit in the vaccination room, took my blood pressure and gave me water and an ice pack. The blood pressure cuff was not the right size, but read my BP as being 117/72. After sitting for about 30 minutes I began to feel better so I went to sit in the observation area again. I waited until it was an hour after I felt sick before leaving to do shopping. I walked the store for about 30 minutes before returning to the pharmacy. I kept getting waves of nausea, heart palpitations, and dizziness and extreme dry mouth, I was feeling very lethargic. By the time I got back to the pharmacy I was begining to feel out of it and decided to call the paramedics. They took my BP again and it was 127/41. I began to shake by the time the paramedics arrived and needed help onto the stretcher to take me out to the ambulance. In the ambulance my BP was 149/85.  I began to feel better on my way to the ER, but kept getting waves of nausea/ feeling like my BP was high/dizziness with the addition of heat flashes. I told the nurses and doctor at the ER that I thought I was having a reaction to my vaccine and described what happened, but they only treated me for nausea and on my discharge papers said I was there because of nausea. They gave me anti-nausea medicine and after a few hours they gave me the option of going home or staying to get I.V fluids. I chose to get I.V. fluids and stayed a few hours longer until I felt less out of it and like the waves of sickness were less intense/ frequent. I continued experiencing waves of sickness until June 9th and spent most of that time on bed rest.
LAB_DATA: CBC: high WBC, low RBC, low Hgb, low Hct LFT's: high All Phos @151 otherwise normal
OTHER_MEDS: Levothyroxine Prenatal vitamin Iron supplement Vitamin C Calcium

Pt received the first dose on 04/30/2021, with no side affects.  She received the second dose, 05/21/21 and tolerated it well that day, the following day she had mild chills and shakes.  Two days after receiving the vaccine she started having episodes of syncope.  When she felt this coming on she would lay down in bed. Had a few episodes where she was nauseas and would vomit.  At approximately 2:00pm she blew her nose and when she did she felt a pop under her right eye. Immediately there was swelling under eye, pockets of blood where bruising started.  She was taken to  Medical Center.  After being seen it was determined that she had a Orbital Floor Blowout in her right eye socket.  She was questioned as to trauma to the eye, abuse, etc. There was none - she had not fallen or hit anything either.  There was no other evidence of an external injury that caused this.  No history of injury to this eye or facial trauma at all. She had to see a plastic surgeon the following day and an ophthalmologist.  She had to have surgery to place a titanium mesh plate under her eye. Follow Up Appointments are still happening.
LAB_DATA: PT was taken to the emergency room where there were many laboratory and diagnostic tests completed. Bloodwork, Urinalysis, MRI CT and Xray.
OTHER_MEDS: Currently taking Propranolol and amitryptaline. Zofran when needed.
HISTORY: History of Lyme's Disease, no current symptoms at time of vaccination. Elevated Pulse treated by propranolol. History of heart attacks, due to lymes carditis.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Four days post-vaccination, she had a serious spell with a hiatal hernia which resulted in a possible gastric volvulus. She recovered enough to extubate and go to a regular room but then ended up back on the vent and in ICU a second time. She was extubated again, but still could not maintain her O2 levels without medical intervention. She passed away on April 3, 2021. She did have covid-19 in late November 2020, with a mild case of pneumonia. This patient received their second Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine on 6/4/2021.  The patient began experiencing arm pain which migrated to his chest on 6/6/2021.  The pain resolved but returned with increased severity on 6/7/2021, prompting medical evaluation.  The pain was described as a pressure sensation in the center of the chest and in bilateral arms.  Upon initial evaluation, he was found to have an abnormal EKG with ST segment changes.  Troponin was significantly elevated.  He was transferred to the hospital.  A transthoracic echo was obtained and was normal.  He was hospitalized on the pediatric cardiology service, admitted on 6/8/2021.  Troponin trended down during his stay. He was started on lisinopril.  He was discharged home on 6/9/2021 with plan for outpatient pediatric cardiology follow up.  Given the proximity of his second Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine to onset of his symptoms, and given similar reported events, the chief concern is whether his episode of myocarditis is related to administration of the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine.  I was on call as attending physician when this patient was admitted.  Physician cared for this patient as the pediatric cardiology inpatient attending during his hospital course.

I was a bit panicked and was thinking that if the feeling didn't go away I'd have to ask my son to call the ambulance.  I'm not given to alarm typically. Received Shot, experienced dizziness, confusion immediately Evening of first day: was tired, did not feel "right".  Next Day: Very tired, but hands and muscles in legs began to ache 2 days after shot: Stomach became severely swollen and painful. Felt like an endometriosis flare. Had extreme diarrhea for three days. Voiding roughly 12 times per day. Sore rectum, lower stomach, intestines. These symptoms of soreness lasted for 3 days or so. 3 days after shot: severe sadness. Crying, couldn't shake it. Pain all over body.   Over the next week my body became more and more sore. My feet began to cramp and fold inwards like they were trying to bend in half. I could not sit on any hard surface as my legs and back hurt too bad to sit on anything but piles of pillows. I could not walk well as my feet were very sore. A week after shot began feeling electric shock feelings throughout my legs. Zaps of electricity. Hands still very sore. Legs felt like I'd lifted weights for a week.   Day 10 following shot still experiencing severe pain. Heart began racing. Resting heart rate would jump to 130 upon standing. Still having episodes of heart racing.  Forearm began spasming and would cause my middle and ring fingers on my right hand to contract and close against my palm. Could not hold right hand steady. Still experiencing pins and needles in hand and arm. Spasming and contractions stopped after a few days.  While I understand that many of these are known side effects, I was also lead to believe that these side effects would last 3 days or so. These have lasted well beyond that window.

My adverse reaction began, I went to the ER March 19th 2021 around noon, I had woken up that morning with a bumpy rash starting across my right buttocks and wrapping around my right ride and down the right side of my leg and also on the top of my right leg. I had thought a spider bit me and I am allergic to spiders but at the ER they did not know if it was an insect bite or something else. They gave me a cortisone shot. I have Medicare and I could not see my Doctor so I waited until Monday and saw him at 4pm. He gave me an antiviral for ten days and it did not do anything for the pain, the rash turned to blisters. I talked to my sister and she had found a topical cream that may help so I started using this derma-change and that really helped. I did not start taking Lyrica until two weeks later. So I had over one week of agony. I have been tapering down my dosage and am down to one 75MG capsule in the morning. My dose period is that I have relief for about 5-6 hours, then I will take another dosage. I expand in my dosage time at the end of the day so I can take one before bed. I might wish this shingles on my very worst enemy but that is it, just one person and it it really is horrible.  It starts out as an itch and then it goes to huge blisters and you have to be very careful because it can spread all over your body. So this is my complication after receiving the Moderna vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Hemoptysis.  On 06/05, a one-time event (old, dark clots) occurred.  On 06/06, there were several instances, some older clots, some lighter/fresher blood.  Then 4 days of no blood, but "normal" (usual) infected sputum colors (preexisting lung infection; see continuation page).  Then on 06/11 beginning @ 7:57am, fresh (light) blood streaks/tinged sputum, which occurred a number of times over the span of approximately 5 hours, until "normal" pale yellow infected sputum was expectorated.  Then on 06/12 beginning @ 9:30am, fresh blood again, which again occurred a number of times over the span of about 5 hours until the usual infected colors of sputum were expectorated. Additional information for Item 18: I have a history of MAI/MAC infection and resultant hemoptysis since 2006.  However, until the first Pfizer dose, it had been 2 years since the last incident of hemoptysis, which was due, at least in large part, to malnutrition spanning a couple of months, for reasons unrelated to the lungs.  I believe my most recent hemoptysis episodes are a result of my immune system being distracted by the Covid-19 vaccine, thus allowing the Mycobacterium avium (and/or other) to more effectively attack my lung tissue.  There was no hemoptysis yesterday (06/13), but this has me concerned about the second dose causing additional, possibly worse, problems for my immune system, as it needs to be concentrating on my lung infection full-time; it has been keeping the MAC (and/or other) generally under control, assuming hemoptysis is a good indicator, which my X-rays over the years of monotherapy with Ethambutol suggest is the case.  I discontinued Ethambutol on 06/15/2012, with no further hemoptysis until 04/26/2019, and then no hemoptysis until 11 days after the first Pfizer Covid-19 dose. It seems reasonable to conclude that the vaccine led to these latest hemoptysis events and perhaps allowed the preexisting bacterial infection to cause additional lung damage.The physician noted above is my current pulmonologist.  I was to have follow-up lung CT scan and lung function tests, but did not do so in 2020 because of Covid-19 concerns.  I had planned to see Dr. and my other doctors after being fully-vaccinated, but since lung function tests cannot be performed on patients with active/recent hemoptysis, this may cause an even further delay in my obtaining appropriate diagnostics and treatment.
CUR_ILL: MAI/MAC, bronchiectasis, mitral, central serous retinopathy
HISTORY: MAI/MAC since 2006, bronchiectasis (02/19/2019 heart calcium CT requires followup lung CT for definitive diagnosis)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 4/18/21 pfizer shot in left arm. 8 hours later nausea, heart race, dizzy. go to sleep. wake normal. no more symptoms for 10 days. Day 10, arm pain returns at the injection site. Day 20 arm pain has spread in size and pain, i cancel the second shot. elbow and wrist become inflamed, tight, pain restricted. become sick for 5 days, headaches exhausted.  prescribed 40mg prednisone for 5 days. first day it took the swelling down, then swelling came right back 2nd day. pinky and ring finder go numb, paresthesia/paresis. nerve pain in forearm to hand. ulnar nerve at first then all fingers. arm injection pain throbbing. rash shows up on stomach (now at 3.5 to 4 weeks since shot) cannot grasp a cup, weakness and numbness in hand. At this time its confined to the injection arm. Over the next week nerve pain and numbness spread to left side of face, both arms, hands, fingers, legs, feet, toes. physical therapist confirms elbow lymph node on injection arm swelling, hands turning red extreme pain and swelling, loss of feeling. nerve pain in the entire body, nerve and muscle spasms in all parts of body. Fingers and does burning at the tips feel like a string is cutting off circulation. Visibly red. Around the 4 week mark, fully unable to lift legs or arms, left half of face numb, zap/jots seizure like hitting my body. go to ER seemingly becoming paralyzed,  within hours strength of legs returns but with numb feet/toes. no diagnosis other than peripheral neuropathy. neck begins to swell, hurts to swallow, throat closing. trying to sleep, throat closed, wake up, completely unable to open throat cant breath. throat episodes lasted about 5 days and resolved. complete insomnia and 24/7tinitus. any attempt to sleep or become tired results in heavy body zaps like hooked to a tenz unit. can't use hands or type, arm to hand seized nerves, feel like shrunken or contracted nerves. PCP prescribes benzos to sleep. this allows some sleep with waking every hour. over the following weeks symptoms seem to improve slowly but still debilitating. today at week 8+ since one shot only, I am able to type again, but with nerve pain and numbness in all fingers. loud tinnitus, numbness in all limbs, episodes of extreme debilitating muscle fatigue come in waves, almost unable to stand agonizing muscle fatigue and nerve zapping. These full body muscle episodes only seem to come in waves of 24 hours, then seem to feel recovering, only to relapse again. injection site pain seems to have wrapped around to the bicep 24/7 pain. unsure if this is nerve or muscle. 3 ER visits, PCP visits, blood tests, no help. I cannot work, constant nerve firing muscle spasms and nerve pain and episodes of weakness so bad you cannot sit without agonizing pain. I am disabled from this and still searching for help

Patient received the vaccine 6/7 during the day, that evening into the next night he developed subjective fevers and chills. Overnight, he had several episodes of NBNB emesis and had some chest pain. By 6/9, his fevers, chills, and chest pain resolved. However on 6/10, he began having chest pain again; this pain was in the middle of his chest, without radiation. It was worse with laying flat and walking around. He went to his pediatrician, who obtained an EKG and checked some labs. Patient had an elevated troponin of 2.04, CKMB of 12, ESR of 31, and BNP of 39. His EKG was normal but he was directed t come to the emergency room for further workup. Repeat troponin that evening showed up trending troponin of 4.77 and patient was admitted for further workup and monitoring. His chest pain resolved and his troponin levels downtrended through the next day (4.77 -> 2.3 -> 0.4). Patient was monitored on telemetry and had no events of arrhythmia. Echocardiogram obtain did not show any evidence of decreased cardiac function. Patient was scheduled to under cardiac MRI (at this time, results of MRI are pending)
LAB_DATA: 6/10/2021: Troponin 2.04 -- > later increased to 4.77.  CKMB 12, ESR 31, BNP 30. 6/11/2021: Troponin 2.3 -- > later decreased to 0.4 6/12/2021: Echocardiogram -- > Normal LV systolic function, normal RV systolic function 6/14/2021: cardiac MRI -- > read pending at time of event reporting.
HISTORY: ADHD (takes adderall during the school year, but was not on it at the time of the vaccination)

A little over two days after my first COVID vaccine, I started experiencing racing thoughts and feelings of heightened anxiety, franticness, panic, agitation and overwhelm. The severity of these symptoms would fluctuate, but they have been present most of the time since then. They made it very difficult to complete my semester at school. A week prior my long-term girlfriend effectively broke up with me, and I had been taking two herbs, Wort and rhodiola, the former for a month and the latter for two weeks at the beginning of symptoms, which I later found out can significantly influence brain chemistry and even induce mania in some individuals. Thus, it seems likely that a combination of these and other factors could have caused the symptoms I am now experiencing, and this is the opinion of the psychiatrist I am currently seeing (listed under doctor to contact). However, given the close timing of my vaccination and subsequent onset of symptoms, I have been worried about whether it could have played a role and wanted to report it. In the past couple weeks the psychiatrist has prescribed me with hydroxizine to help me sleep and GABA to help calm my mind, and they have helped a bit, but I still do not feel like myself.

Within 24 hours of receiving his 2nd vaccination, my son began complaining about heart pain. He described them as sporadic, and mild in nature - mostly an annoyance. He has never experienced anything similar in the past and is in exceptionally good health (He runs long distance cross country and track for his high school). Three days from his vaccination, I took him to his primary care physician where the performed and ECG which the doctor interpreted as "normal", and most likely not Myocarditis. He recommended Advil (3 tablets up to 4 times a day) for a few days, to reduce any potential inflammation, which he began immediately.   Once he began the Advil regiment, his conditions ceased to come back and he has not experienced any further episodes even after he stopped taking Advil. The night of the vaccine I spiked a fever of 103.0 that lasted 3 days along with chills, vomiting and body aches. On May 10th I started having problems breathing, I was having coughing fits, trouble getting air and was brought to the emergency room on on May 11th. They did chest xrays, have me albuterol treatments and steroids and sent me home. I tried to go to work on May 13th ( I work at a doctors office) and I was immediately sent to the hospital as I went into respiratory distress with my oxygen levels in the low 80's. I was given more steroids, IV steroids and sent home with an inhaler. I went to my primary care physician for a follow up on May 17th  I was still having trouble breathing, was given 2 breathing treatments at the doctors office and then they called an ambulance for me to take me to the hospital for respiratory distress. I was admitted to the hospital for 4 days where I was given 2 IVs, more chest x-rays, a CT, I.V. steroids, epinephrine,  and breathing treatments every 3-4 hours or as needed. At one point they considered intubating me to let my lungs rest as I could not breathe and would cough until I vomited. No one could figure out the cause and assume it was a vaccine reaction. I was then sent home with at home Duo nebulizer treatments, inhaled steroids, and cough syrup. I also had a lung function test done.
LAB_DATA: 3 chest x-rays that were clear, CT scan that was clear, 4 Negative covid test, lots of blood work that I do not know the results of and a lung function test that I have not gotten the results back from yet
OTHER_MEDS: Carbamazepine, Trazodone, Levothyroxine, Singular, Colazapam, Labetalol

Within 15 minutes of the first dose I experienced itching on my face, which intensified with time.  By later in the day, I had itching on my upper body.  In addition, I experienced fatigue, swollen glands and generally felt "bad."  Within a few days, I started to have joint pain throughout my body, which continued for several days.    After my second shot, I experienced some itching, but less than with the first shot.  However, within 2 days, I had joint pain throughout my body.  The pain was "matched" on both sides and I had pain in my knees, hips, shoulders, elbows, wrists and knuckles.  There was no swelling in the joints and they were not "hot" to the touch.  I did not have fever.  The pain was intense enough that I began to take 15 mg. of  Meloxicam (an anti-inflammatory drug) daily, supplemented by regular doses of Tylenol to reduce the pain.  I was able to complete daily tasks, but found it difficult to do so.  The amount of pain that I experienced interfered with my ability to go to sleep and stay asleep.   The joint pain continued for 2 full weeks after the second shot and gradually began to get better by the third week after the second shot.  I saw my primary care doctor during the 3rd week and because I have a family history of rheumatoid arthritis, she ordered a series of labs to test for RA, as well as other conditions that could cause continued joint pain.   All came back negative.  My joint pain continued to improve as time passed, with almost all of the pain gone by the first week of June.  I am now able to do daily activities and take no medication for inflammation or pain.

On Sunday, April 18th I did a telehealth appointment and was diagnosed with shingles. I took Valtrex for 7 days and after about 2 weeks the blisters began to heal.  My period was supposed to start on Wednesday, May 12th and usually lasts 5 days (end Sunday, May 16th). I just completed my next cycle which came as expected on June 9th and ended 5 days later on June 13th.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 24 hours, I began experiencing the usual symptoms associated with 2nd dose, including chills, fever, body aches, etc.  Within 72 hours, I began experiencing serious chest pain, radiating pain into back and shoulders, and numbness in left arm--all symptoms associated with a heart attack.  I was immediately taken to the emergency department where I was treated with pain killer for chest pain and given a blood thinner and IV fluids.   EKG and chest X-ray were normal.  Blood work indicated highly elevated troponin levels thereby indicating significant stress to heart muscle.  Treatment included prescribing medications including Lopressor, Lipitor, and aspirin.  Following stay in the hospital, I was released with no signs of heart complications.  I'm continuing the medications for general maintenance and prevention.  Prognosis is good with no further complications and no further threat of a future heart attack based on current medical conditions.

EKG, chest X-ray, and echocardiogram results were normal.  Angiogram indicated 40% blockage and was deemed mild blockage with no need for a stent.  Blood work indicated highly elevated troponin levels thereby indicating significant stress to heart muscle.

I got my vaccine around 11:40 am. Within 5 minutes of the vaccine, I could feel that my face was hot and had tingling sensation under the skin around my cheek. I was sent behind the curtain with a Emergency doctor. At the time, the symptom did not get worse, so I was discharged. When I got back to my place and was in my meeting around 1:45 pm, something felt weird around my lips and my tongue. I could feel that my tongue was swelling, so as my lips  I got scared so I took another dose of Xyzal. I could still feel that swelling was progressing. My colleagues told me that I was talking as if I couldn't feel my tongue and my tongue wasn't moving as I was talking. I remembered the doctor at the vaccine site told me to call 911 if the symptoms got worse. So I called 911, paramedics came. Epipen wasn't necessary, but I took another dose of Xyzal. Other than my blood pressure being shot up, my vitals were okay. They did confirm the allergic reaction but told me that they cannot confirm that it is from the vaccine. However, I have never had such a reaction in my life, I highly believe that it was from the vaccine. The swelling did not go away for 7 days. And during the time, I was taking at least 15 mg of Xyzal per day to keep the itchiness and swelling down.  I reached out to my PCP and he advised not to get the second dose.
OTHER_MEDS: One tablet (5mg) of Xyzal 2 hours prior to vaccination.

This feeling is not continual but persistent.  The feeling "moves around" the legs and the following day that area will be sore.  On May 13, received second dose of Pfizer vaccine; the leg feeling remains constant but has lessened in severity, but some days the feeling worsens. Has been to the doctor twice.  First visit blood panel and Lyme Disease test obtained. On June 18th, had Ultra Sound of legs performed for vascular study; has not heard results. States contacted testing facility and results had not been sent to his ordering physician, but "someone there are read the report" and supposedly normal.  Is scheduled for an EMG on 6/24/21.  Encouraged client to monitor symptoms and if leg pain / spasm worsen or other symptoms arise, to seek out ER care.

Per hospital intake, the patient had ventricular fibrillation cardiac arrest in the field just a few hours after receiving his second Pfizer COVID 19 vaccination. EMS was called, and 20 minutes of CPR were administered, prior to achieving ROSC. Patient was sedated and intubated and taken into Hospital. Cooling protocol was initiated and CT angio did not show any evidence of pulmonary embolism. Patient also underwent cardiac catheterization, which was was negative for clear intracardiac or coronary abnormalities or stenoses. Ultimately, the patient was transferred to medical center for implantation of AICD device. No other obvious source or etiology of arrest, but did think worth reporting given temporal proximity to vaccination.

By 2 am on Friday, June 11th, vomiting and diarrhea began. Patient was given 200 mg of Tylenol and 25 mg of Benadryl. Arnaca gel was applied to the rash that formed on the vaccine site. The rash was approximately 3 cm wide and 5 cm tall oval shape. It was bright red and painful to touch (like a sunburn). Arm was also swollen from shoulder to elbow. Patient slept from 4 am - 8am on 6/11. All day on 6/11 patient had trouble keeping down fluids (tried water, juice, gatorade, and broth) and patient refused food (tried popsicles, rice, bananas, scrambled eggs, and plain noodles). Patient complained of throbbing pain in left arm. Patient refused to massage the area and would screen in pain and cry with tears if mom touched it at all. Cold packs and warm packs brought no relief. Patient continued to receive Tylenol every four hours. Fever would reach 102-102.5, break with sweats. Patient reported feeling very cold and then very hot. Fever break would last 30 min - 1 hour before climbing again.   Sunday 6/12 continued the same as 6/11. Patient began alternating Advil 200 mg with Tylenol every four hours. Advil didn't seem to help any more than the Tylenol did.  Parent called consulting nurse and was advised to take patient to urgent care where she received anti-nausea medication.  Monday 6/13 patient continues to have difficulty with food and drink. The phenergan meds help with nausea but make patient so tired, there's little chance to get patient to eat or drink. Vomiting has stopped but diarrhea continues.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I received the vaccine in the afternoon and did fine in the evening aside from a low grade fever. The next morning at 10:30 AM I experienced severe nausea and my BP was dropping. I was taking care of a patient at work at the time. I went ahead and got the nurses to take care of my patient. I laid down for a little until the nausea passed The entire time I was very fatigued. I slept for an hour in my car. Then went back to work. I went home at 1:30PM because I felt so bad. I slept when I got home and into the next day. I had nausea, vomiting and diarrhea. I called in sick on Thursday and Friday and stayed in bed the whole time. I also had a swollen lymph node in my right clavicle area. I was still sick in bed all weekend all through Tuesday. The entire time I also experienced shortness of breath. I still experience the shortness of breath.  The shortness of breath was so bad I couldn't go a few feet to grab something with out having to take a rest. The shortness of breath has gotten me to a point where wearing a mask is difficult for me which was never the case. After having surgery, My stats kept dropping which is unusual for me. I also experienced pain in my shoulders. It feels like I am carrying a heavyweight backpack on my shoulder. I also am now experiencing chest wall pain. If I move around, I feel pain. It got to a point where I had to take a pain pill from my surgery and that did not help. I am scheduled for a echo on Thursday.
LAB_DATA: Chest XRAY: normal EKG: normal  Vitamin D: low (8), abnormal

Patient is a 46 year old male who admitted to hospital for Facial nerve palsy. Patient felt with left sided facial droop and tingling sensation for 2 days. He reported symptoms onset at 1330 on 6/10/2021 while driving a truck. He also had left sided occipital headache and rested for 1 hour. His symptoms improved after the nap but never resolved completely. He got into a location and rested there for 1 night. In the morning after waking up he was having difficulty chewing food on his left side. He called EMS and was brought to hospital. While in the ED, he received workup including CT Head W/O, CTA Head/Neck with perfusion scan that were all negative. Other labs obtained included BMP, CBC, Troponin x1, Coag studies & CXR which were largely unremarkable. Neurology were called for stroke alert and given ASA 325mg and ordered MRI. Patient's MRI was unremarkable for stroke or masses. He was started on Prednisone 40mg once daily for Facial Nerve Palsy. He was seen by physical therapy and occupational therapy, they recommended him go home to family. His symptoms improved after therapies were initiated but are not completely resolved. Patient will continue taking his home medications per his primary care doctor. He will complete a 7 day steroid course, has 3 days remaining. He will take Acyclovir 5 times per day for 10 days. We also gave him lubricating eye drops since he continues to have difficulty closing his left eye.  He spends a lot of time outdoors and works with horses. He reports getting tick bites before in his body but never noticed a rashes. He has never received treatment for Lyme Disease. He is a long-haul truck driver and has driven all around. He reports walking in wooded areas when he stops in the rest area. We obtained Lyme Titers, which were eqivocal for IgM and negative for IgG. Western blot was ordered to rule out Lyme disease. He should followup with PCP for treatment if he is positive. We will call him with results when available.   Of note he received Pfizer 2nd COVID vaccine on 6/9/21 (LOT #EW0178). He reported fever and diarrhea that night and next morning. He then reports having presenting symptoms after 7 hours of driving. We also believe the cause of his facial nerve paralysis could have been a side effect of his vaccination.

June 14, 2021   This E-Mail concerns continuing ?side effects? from the second shot of the Moderna vaccine.   I received the second shot on May 11.   Today is June 14.  So, I am writing this report 5 weeks after the last shot, with many of the effects continuing.  I am 64 yr. old male.  I have a history of high blood pressure, which has been controlled successfully with medication for the past 8 years.  I had a hemorrhagic stroke in 2013, successfully recovered.  Otherwise no severe disease-type medical risks, I am health and physically fit.  I live with serious chronic pain from a multitude of factors.   I have severe tendinitis-type problems in my arms and legs; joint stiffness and pain, tight muscle problems.  The vaccine ?attacked? and severely worsened these symptoms.  The night of the vaccination, I started getting serious pain in a number of painful areas ? knees, ankles, elbows and forearms, like inflammation, all at once.  This pain advanced to injuries in prior injured areas, like knees forearms lower legs, and worsened when I would try basic loosening up exercises, to point that I could barely walk for a couple of weeks.  After exercising or loosening up, muscles and joints would tighten up severely, exacerbating pain and function.   I was barely able to walk or do much for a week or more.  I?ve needed extra bodywork and chiropractic sessions to deal with this.  The problem with tendinitis areas is less bad than right after the shot but still significantly worse than it had been before the vaccine.  When exercising, I am slower and able to do less time at cardio functions and have to lift 10-20 lbs. less weight when using weight machines.  I also get joint pain, ala knees when I use exercise bike; knees and shoulders get a certain type of pain (I feel it on the outside of the joint).  These are quantifiable factors.  The joint problems mirror a type of joint problem I had for a couple of years after my stroke, not what I experience every day.  The joint is weaker, and I feel a vague pain like the pain is coming from outside of the joint.   So, the vaccine seems to have ?attacked? and exacerbated problem areas of mine which already affect my ability to function adequately, and it is unclear whether or not these will fully resolve.  It is not a ?one or two-day? thing as suggested.    Additionally, I?ve generally felt drowsiness and ?headachy? during the day since.  These symptoms have lessened, but still there to some extent.  It is unclear whether or not I will fully recover or if anything else is wrong.  I am doubtful that I should take any additional ?booster shots? later if suggested or mandated.  Your attention to this matter is very much appreciated.
LAB_DATA: none; I am getting chiropractic services and deep tissue massage for some of the symptoms, no M.D. care otherwise
OTHER_MEDS: losartan and amlodipine, both for hypertension
CUR_ILL: no specific illnesses at time of vaccine or recently before.  chronic and severe pain syndromes and injuries from such are ongoing problems and what the vaccine exacerbated the most.
HISTORY: hypertension, well controlled with medication for past 8 years
ALLERGIES: many, too ,many to list;  multiple foods, environmental, and most pharmaceutical drugs cause significant problems for me - I take as few as possible and seek holistic care.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 53 yo woman with no PMH was diagnosed with COVID-19 by PCR on 5/7/21. She had a mild illness with cough and fevers but did not require hospitalization. Her symptoms lasted about 1 week. She got her first dose of Pfizer COVID vaccine on 5/29 around 11 am. Within 4 hours (around 3 pm) she started to develop extreme fatigue, which she attributed to vaccine. This was followed by nausea, vomiting and diarrhea later that same day. The symptoms got worse on 5/30. Her diarrhea/GI symptoms resolved on 5/31. That day, she had a fever to 101.3. She continued to have fatigue, and started to have dyspnea, and presented to hospital on 6/1/21. On arrival to ED her vitals were 88/41, 36.1, 125, 18, 95% on RA (13:22). She become more hypotensive with nadir BP 63/48, HR 109 at 17:30, at which time she was started on norepinephrine. Physical exam at admission was notable for clear lungs, tenderness to palpation in the midepigastric and LUQ areas, and the absence of rash. Admission labs: WBC 31.3, Hb 14.2, Hct 43.0, Plt 144, MCV 96, 85% neutrophils, BNP 3117, Na 132, K 3.8, CO2 19, Cl 95, BUN 35, Create 4.62, gluc 133, protein 6.1, alb 2.2, TB 5.5, DB 2.9, Alk phos 159, ALT 47, AST 33, lactate 4.2, troponin I 0.047, random cortisol 93. Strep pneumo and legionella antigens negative. Hepatitis serologies, HIV test, all negative. COVID test by PCR was positive on 6/1/21. She was admitted to the ICU. The day following admission (6/2) CRP 32.4, ESR 106, LDH 399, ferritin 1626, procalcitonin 54.85. CT A/P unremarkable except for bilateral patchy airspace opacities. RUQ US unremarkable, including Dopplers. Echocardiogram (TTE) with LV systolic function mod-severely globally reduced, EF 35%, no valvular disease. Dopplers of LE showed small non-occlusive thrombus in R common femoral. The patient was seen by Infectious Diseases on HD#2 (6/2/21) and IVIG was recommended and administered due to suspicion for MIS-A. She had also been started on cefepime, vancomycin and metronidazole on admission. Blood, urine and resp cultures were negative. She continued to have high norepinephrine requirements, reaching 0.34 mcg/kg/min on 6/3. Due to ongoing shock (cardiogenic vs septic), a Swan-Ganz was placed on 6/4/21. RAP 11 mmHg, RV 38/10 mmHg, PA 40/20 (27) mmHg, PCWP 19 mm Hg, CO 5.75, CI 2.8, SVR 1100, MvO2: 70%. These were consistent with distributive/septic shock rather than cardiogenic.  The patient was able to be weaned from pressors on 6/5/21 at 11:55. Throughout her entire hospital stay, she was comfortable with no respiratory distress, and no abnormalities in mentation. She was transferred to the general medical floor and completed 7 days of antibiotics for empiric sepsis treatment. Labs at discharge on 6/8 showed procalcitonin 5.43, CRP 8.8, LDH 362, Ferritin 1511, TP 5.9, ALT 17, AST 29, Alk phs 158, TB 1.3, Alb 1.6, Create 0.98, WBC 32.5, Hb 7.8, Hct 22.9, Plt 100, neutrophils 70%. She was feeling well without complaints, and will follow up as an outpatient. She was prescribed Xarelto for DVT.

I had my first Pfizer vaccine on March 27th.  Around April 9th I began to feel chest pain.  I went to the ER on April 13th and they initially thought I was having a heart attack.  Ultimately I was in the ICU overnight with pericarditis, which effected my heart rate.  I had several EKGs, blood tests and an Echocardiogram.  I was sent home with meds for three weeks.  I had my second doze of Pfizer vaccine on April 24th.  I was back in the ER on May 24th, sent home yet back again on May 31st after a week of heart rate issues.  I started in the ICU, stayed overnight in the hospital and then send home with meds for four weeks.  The diagnosis was a return of the pericarditis.  I?m now in recovery mode.  My concern is basically a healthy sixty-six year old male with no heart issues ended up in the ICU with pericarditis just over two weeks after the Pfizer vaccine and then back again the next month after I had received the recommendation to go live life with no needs of a follow-up appointment needed from the cardiologist.
LAB_DATA: EKGs, Blood Work and Echhocardiogram,,,no damage was done to the heart apparently.
HISTORY: I had hepatitis in 1965 apparently from a clam.  Then around one decade ago, I was diagnosed with ITP, which is low platelets (mine are around 80 and should be over 100 (ideally 150sih)...I've never had any negative repercussions from having ITP.

She got her vaccine, she came home and was fine.  Her mother had her APT and she herself was a little bit dizzy and she took her mother for her vaccine APT.  Then they went to the mall and she just started not to feel good, and had a stomach ache, diarrhea and left due to her not feeling well.  That night she just started to feel horrible, and at 6:22 AM was was not feeling well, and had every single symptom of the reactions, brain fog as well.  She also had a fever up to 101.5 at 12:55 PM on 4/1/21.  She progressed to getting sicker, shortness of breath and worsening symptoms with highest temp of 101.7.   On 4/2/21 she started feeling better and her fever was normalizing and had cold sweats, and the initial symptoms of nausea would come and go and still had stomach issues for days afterwards, but the fever did not come back.  Then she started having chest pains, shortness of breath that lasted for 3 weeks afterwards.  She went to the UC on 4/14/21 and vomited again and got concerned that she was still having the chest pains and was getting sicker.  She informed them at the UC that she believed she was having symptoms related to the vaccine and the doctor there had informed her that it could not have been related to the vaccine and "written off" and nothing else was said about the vaccine after that.  She never saw a Dr., they did do an EKG and was told that it was normal and was told that she was going to send her to the ER "as she matters".   She informed them that she did not want to go to the ER and was informed that she would be seen right away as she was not feeling well enough with the nausea and sick.  The ER was packed and was triaged and they told her that she would be seen and none of that happened.  She supposedly got triaged and had an EKG and was informed that she would be written off about it and that they were making it a political thing.  She had an IV line inserted, and had blood drawn and after 2 hours nothing had been done.  After about 3 1/2 hours being in the ER and after she had made a big fuss and was put in a room.  They sent somebody in and informed her that she had a cardiologist in her family and a GP and if they weren't going to see her to let her go home.  She was then sent in another nurse who was more understanding and he went over the EKG with her and told her that it was strange and said that her heart beat was normal, and then at some point that it skipped a bit and then had a subsequent EKG and that was abnormal as well but in a different way.  Then another nurse came in and told her that they wanted to run tests every hour and never mentioned to admit her, for her to stay in the ER but did not feel they were comfortable sending her home, and that her shortness of breath was concerning to her.  She was progressively feeling worse and was not seen by a cardiologist and they sent her home to FU with one.    She went to see a cardiologist and by then it was documented that there were some people were having heart issues from the vaccine.  He then ordered her an echocardiogram and a stress test, and then did not hear anything from the office.  They had not gotten an authorization from the insurance company and she called her insurance company and they informed them that she was approved and that she is to have an urgent stress test.  At this point she does not know what's going on.   Subsequent to the vaccine she has had normal EKG's for 5 years, and now since the vaccine she has not felt well, she has insomnia, anxiety, fatigue, depression, shortness of breath and chest pains every day and has abnormal EKG's. I called my  family doctor that morning and they had me come into the office, and they did an EKG , and got the same results . I was sent to a heart doctor two days later, and I was still experiencing these issues. I had a stress test done which showed everything was normal.  But last week June 7th, had these palpitations again. The heart doctor only said maybe it's your inhaler. I saw my family doctor today and she indicated that this is not from an inhaler. I did mention the time line of the Covid vaccine and the heart issues, and she did not rule that out either.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I got the vaccine in the morning.  That night I was unable to fall asleep the whole night.  A few weeks went by and then I started experiencing occasional insomnia.  I would wake up in the middle of the night and be unable to go back to sleep.  It kept getting worse such that I could not fall asleep without taking a sleeping pill.  What happens is that when I lay down after about 10 to 15 minutes I start to feel a surge of energy.  My body gets hot.  It is not a fever.  My heart seems to beat faster and my mind is racing.  My doctor prescribed both Ambien and Lunesta.   I take one or the other and eventually I go to sleep.  I am averaging about 4 hours of sleep at night after I take the drug.   The stress of not being able to sleep well has given me some anxiety issues.  In addition, the anxiety has led me to develop high blood pressure.   I am now taking high blood pressure medicine.   I am not the kind of person who has anxiety normally.   I believe the vaccine introduced something into my system that is triggered every night now preventing me from natural sleep.
LAB_DATA: I thought maybe it was that my thyroid had been destabilized by the vaccine and was causing the insomnia.  I went to a specialist who ran tests and evaluated my thyroid saying that it was fine.   This was in May.  I have gone to two different insomnia specialists.  They prescribed additional medicines including hydroxyzine HCL.  Most doctors have told me that they have no idea what side effects from the vaccine are because there has been no studies.  One doctor told me that he had another patient with the same symptoms of ongoing insomnia that came from the vaccine.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On or about April 28, I began feeling what felt like a charlie horse no bigger than the size of a fingertip behind my right leg knee.  It came and went until it was steady about a week later.  In the following weeks, the feeling changed to a burning or jolting pain and spread from the knee both upward and downward the right leg.  Because the event on 4/28 was so close to the 3-week mark after my vaccine and because it was strange but not painful, I didn't report or associate it with the vaccine.  As it grew,  I became more concerned that it wouldn't go away on its own.  Around the week of May 24th, the pain spread down to the ankle and up to my thigh becoming more painful over the days.  After speaking w/ nurse line and my Pharmacist, I drove myself to the ER on June 5th.  A sonogram revealed an engorged main vein but no clots and a CT scan revealed no evidence of Fiskars.  I was released with the advice to take Tylenol/Ibuprofen and to follow up with the vascular surgeon.  By June 7th, I was unable to get out of bed drinking water and taking both meds to relieve pain.  On 6/8, I called 911 and went back to ER.  I had overdosed on aspirin and was treated for 2 days.  An MRI revealed a bulging herniated disk.  I am getting physical therapy and seeing Dr. on July 15th who will be the best contact after that date.
LAB_DATA: All tests and results are online and can be accessed thru the hospital website  You have my permission to access those tests.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 13 yo M with a history of autoimmune hepatitis who presents with 1 day of fever, headache, altered mental status, and vomiting. He received his 2nd Pfizer Covid vaccine on 6/12 and began having symptoms the next night. He began taking ibuprofen for headache and fever. His symptoms worsened through the day until he had vomiting. He was saying strange things and behaving oddly. He became very hot and agitated at home, prompting mom to bring him into an outside hospital ED.  There, rectal temperature was 106F and he was noted to be combative.  A CMP was obtained, which was mostly normal. CT of his head was obtained, during which he had an episode of left upper extremity shaking concerning for seizure. He was reportedly alert throughout.   Patient is a 13 yo M with a history of autoimmune hepatitis who presents with 1 day of fever, headache, altered mental status, vomiting, found to have cerebral edema and elevated CRP. There is no acidosis, elevated lactate, or metabolic derangement, and utox is neg. The etiology could be related to the vaccine. Ingestions are also possible given the high fever and altered mental status - particularly serotonin syndrome. Infectious etiologies are also possible given the fever.   Treatments: hypertonic saline given x1 EEG started Tox screen negative Ceftriaxone and vanc given
LAB_DATA: 6/13/2021 CT cerebral edema  CRP of 4 MRI pending
OTHER_MEDS: ursodiol 500 mg oral tablet 1 tab PO BID azathioprine 75 mg 1 tab PO  allopurinol 100 mg oral tablet 1 tab PO ergocalciferol 1 cap PO
PRIOR_VAX: Pfizer COVID Vaccine #1, headache and fever. Otherwise no reactions.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: An hour and a half after receiving the first dose of the vaccine, I started experiencing pressure on the front of my throat, but I ignored it. I thought it was just a sore throat that I was getting. I had been having sore throats on and off for months. Now that I'm thinking about it, I could have had a reaction immediately after getting the vaccine. I dismissed my high heart rate as anxiety. I started to feel weak and I have an apple watch and I checked my heart rate and it jumped to the mid 130's right after I received the vaccine. I had a weird day where I felt like I had insomnia. My stomach was hurting and I couldn't sleep. The next day, my arm swelled from my elbow to my shoulder. I was very tired throughout the day and had a headache. On 03/29/2021, I went to see my doctor and he told me that I had COVID arm. He told me to not worry about it and told me to make sure I received my 2nd dose. My arm became worse after that. The following day, I started having joint pain, with heart palpitations. I experience costochondritis, from time to time, and when I would breathe in, I would have pressure. During all of this time, the pressure in my throat continued for all of these days. My PCP, ordered me to have a test to have my throat looked at. I started having numbness and pinching pains on my left side. The left side of my face became numb. I felt like someone had run me over with a car on my left side. My whole left side of my body was in pain. I went to have my throat ultrasound. They noticed a small nodule and did a biopsy. The doctor said that he thought I had a lot of inflammation in my throat because I felt the needle as he injected it into my throat. I started to become very worried about choking to death. I went to and ENT and he took a scope down my throat and said that I have a lot of inflammation. I went to the ER on 04/15 at 11PM and I was there until 5AM on 04/16. I went because of the constant pain I was experiencing. I was having to swallow to breathe. They provided me with some medicine in an IV, maybe an anti-inflammatory, and it helped. After receiving this I could feel things starting to slow down. I'm not sure if it was the medicine or that this had run it course. I could finally breath again though. By the time this has happened, it was time for my second dose. I called my allergist and asked him to test me before I got my 2nd dose. I went in and that is when he confirmed that I am allergic to polyethylene glycol (PEG). My doctor and I decided to do an antibody test to see if the first vaccine helped at all. I'm hoping that I'm able to receive a booster vaccine.
LAB_DATA: I had a throat ultrasound, a biopsy, blood work and an allergy test.
OTHER_MEDS: I was taking vitamin D and possibly a multivitamin.
CUR_ILL: I did not have any other illnesses at the time.
PRIOR_VAX: I had an adverse event after receiving the flu vaccine in 2012. I cannot remember what event I experienced, but it was very seri
ALLERGIES: I am allergic to amoxicillin, penicillin, I'm sensitive to azithromycin, allergic to melons. I have learned after receiving the vaccine that I am allergic to polyethylene glycol.

As soon as we got home, he was walking toward his bedroom and he say "whoa" and then fell to his knees as I caught him and fainted.  He was passed out for a few seconds.  I called 911 immediately  and then he came to and said "what happened".  Fire Dept. took blood pressure, which was 152/74 and heart rate at 136.  They said his heart rate was fast.  I drove him to ER at and he had a very fast heart rate, around 150 -170.  He was able to go home around 10pm after the negative tests and heart rate coming down to 80-90s for a short time, but still would get high. My son kept saying he felt fine even after passing out and at the ER. He did not feel  like he had a fast heart rate.  ER recommended purchase a pulse oxi meter to test heart rate at home, which I purchased the next day and he's been in the normal range.  He is scheduled to take the 2nd dose June 18th, but I will not let him get it since he had a severe reaction to the 1st dose.
LAB_DATA: did blood tests for myocarditis, blood clots, diabetes, thyroid etc. and came out negative

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Fifteen hours after the vaccine my son woke up and his respiratory rate was high. It was over 140. I woke him up and he had chills and diarrhea. Because of his Cortisol Deficiency I called his doctor. I was advised to give him 30mg Hydrocortisone and lots of water.  His Respiratory and heart rate were high. He was feeling a little short of breath and he had heart palpitations. We went to the ER and they did lots of testing. He had a fever and Sepsis testing. All results were normal and they gave him a Liter of fluids. He was discharged after two hours and his pulse was still high at 105-110. We monitored him and his heart rate was slowing and he started to feel better. His Endocrinologist had him take a double dose of Hydrocortisone the next day. His improvement progressed and by the fourth day the symptoms were gone.  He was able to do his normal activities but tired and worn out from the ordeal. One week later he had a slightly elevated heart rate but it resolved quickly.  He had had a local reaction in his arm with swelling and a rash after the first vaccine.
OTHER_MEDS: Prevacid 30mg/twice daily Levothyroxine 62.5mcg daily, Diamox 375mg/ 2X daily Hydrocortisone 7.5mg/2Xdaily Advair 230/22 two puffs twice daily Fluticasone Spray Xyzal 2.5mg daily
HISTORY: Asthma Cortisol Deficiency GERD Hypothyroidism Pseudotumor Cerebri

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client came to vaccination site at 1715 for his 2nd Pfizer dose on 06/13/21.  After being seated with RN, he expressed concern about receiving his 2nd dose due to the reactions he experienced after receiving his 1st dose.  RN requested Lead RN speak with the client regarding his concerns.  At 1720 Lead RN spoke to client.  Client stated that 1 � days after getting his 1st dose, he experienced soreness & tenderness in the axillary area of the left arm.  Client stated that 3 days later his axillary area began swelling.  The swelling continued below his axillary down the left side of his abdomen and onto the left side of his back.  Client stated the pain level was a 4 on a scale of 0-10.  He also stated there was no discoloration or redness in any of the areas where he experienced swelling.  On day 10 the left side of the client?s neck began to swell.  He also started to experience discomfort at the injection site and arm fatigue.  Client stated at no time did he experience any trouble breathing, shortness of breath, or chest pain.  Client stated he has been dieting and lost 145 lbs. in the last year.  He previously had high blood pressure, but no longer does.  He also stated the only other underlying conditions he has is a thyroid problem (hypothyroidism), and he is not medication compliant.  Over the last 6 months he has only taken his levothyroxine intermittently.  In the last 2 months he has not taken any of his levothyroxine until a few days ago.  Client takes no other medication, but is allergic to penicillin-based antibiotics.  Client stated he gets dizzy, hallucinates, and swells up in various places on his body.  However, he does not experience shortness of breath or trouble breathing.  Client did not take any medication for the side effects he experienced after receiving his first Pfizer injection or seek medical treatment.  Client stated all the swelling began to subside on day 17.  Lead RN performed a medical consult with Clinical Care Coordinator who authorized moving forward with administering client a Pfizer 2nd dose in the opposite arm with a 30-minute observation.  Prior to RN administering vaccine, Lead RN educated client on normal vs adverse effects of the vaccine.  Lead RN confirmed with client that he has access to a HCP for follow-up, if needed.  Lead RN also recommended client follow-up with his HCP regarding his hyperthyroid condition.  Lead RN instructed client to seek emergency care if he experienced shortness of breath, trouble breathing, or chest pain at any time after leaving the vaccination facility.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I suspect I had a mild case of myocarditis - the morning after my second COVID shot, I woke up with a heart rate over 100bpm (according to my Apple Watch). My normal resting rate is about 60bpm, so this was a huge jump. Even though I spent most of the day in bed, my heart rate continued to be over 100bpm. In addition, I had chest pain in my heart area (it hurt every time I breathed deeply), along with a 100 degree Fahrenheit fever, chills, and aches. Most symptoms went away after a day of first appearing, however my chest pain persisted for another 3-4 days. The first day I worked out after my second shot (~9 days after), I also had heart pain that I had never experienced before. I did not go to the doctor as I thought it would go away on its own, which it eventually did after about 12 days after my second shot.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I was fine until the following day felt some tingling in my fingertips and feet. Then the day after that, my face has some tingling. By Monday, the left side of my face was feeling numb when I went to work and as the week went on the tingling became worse and became more painful. The pain went from my jaw up the left side of my face, pain across and was traveling up my head pass my temple (up to my forehead). I was diagnosed at the hospital with Trigeminal Neuralgia. I started to get shooting pain across my back (happened the second week just out of nowhere and I'm the type of person that waits to see what would happen and then it slowly, after a few weeks, went to the lower right side of my back. So, I thought it was from the way I was sleeping and then on June 3rd, I went to my Doctor because the pain had started to radiate down the front/back of my leg and my hip on the right side of my body (leg and hip); therefore, I went to my PCP. He gave me what he though (complete physical) his clinical diagnosis was since I had nerve trouble (possibly related to nerve inflammation and he wanted to see because it was not a disc or anything else...nerves have become inflamed). He give me a steroid shot and give me oral steroids and if after I took them that if I didn't feel the pain anymore in my nerves it was because my nerves became inflamed. The pain has gone away and I am keeping my fingers crossed that it does not happen again. My Doctor and I do believe that before COVID came out that I was very ill and I had all the COVID symptoms. I went and at that time there was no testing available. The Doctor basically tested me and feels that I may have had COVID since he tested me for Strep Throat the last week of February 2020.
LAB_DATA: The Doctor did clinical testing to make sure that my smile was symmetrical and asked if I wanted a CT Scan; however, it was not necessary and I opted not to do the CT Scan (was told that if the diagnosis of Trigeminal Neuralgia continued that I would need to see a Neurologist). It took about two weeks and it was fully gone.
OTHER_MEDS: I am on Lexapro and Klonipin every single day.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Initial adverse event was severe sickness the day after the vaccine.  I was extremely ill for 3-4 days after the vaccine with flu like symptoms.  Fever, chills, body aches, head ache.  1-2 weeks after that I developed extreme joint pain in two specific areas.  My left index finger knuckle, and my right knee.  My index finger had extreme pain, was sensitive to touch, and would lock into position as I slept requiring me to gradually wiggle it (painfully) to gain function in the morning.    My right knee became very sore to the point that it was hard to walk my dog, and the knee felt unstable and painful with any twisting or torquing moves.  The two conditions persisted for 2 months before worsening.  The specific pain moved from the middle knuckle of my index figure to the base knuckle, the pain in my knee also spread to a sharp pain in my ankle, and I developed a specific pain (exact location) in my head that would hurt when I coughed, bent over or clenched (like when peeing).  At that point I went to the doctor to be checked out.
LAB_DATA: Blood tests for auto immune response have been ordered 06/14/2021 but the results have not come back yet.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After the first dose FN6206 in my left arm, I got a quarter size hive near my left wrist and some red spots on my right wrist. I showed the nurse the photos of my first dose and she asked me to stay for 30-45 minutes to be sure I was OK. We decided to do this one in the right arm.  After the 2nd dose, the large hive went away, didn't return.  But then I got a rash on both arms between my wrist and elbow.  Smallish red dots with a few pinhead sized clusters like I had with Covid.   The sores during covid (Nov 7, 2020, positive test Nov 12) were on my fingers/hand. I had what I would say is a mild version of covid with about a week of illness, one symptom at a time, no respiratory. Teeny headache, minor throat irritation, 1 day of body aches, 24 hour fever 99.5, couple days of fatigue, couple weeks of queasiness, loss of taste/smell for about 75 days and the little hand/finger breakouts plus a rash on my lower legs that looked like razor burn or tiny blister-like things.  I have been keeping a diary since March 1,2020.

A few days after the first vaccine I had chest tightness, especially on the left side and middle of my chest that came out of nowhere (no runny nose or anything). It felt like my lungs were irritated and I was short of breath, very tired. Worried it might be covid I went to get tested and it came back negative. Monocytes were high and the doctor suspected early pneumonia. Chest x ray came back without signs of pneumonia (but I continued the antibiotics for 10 days just in case it had been too early to show on the X-ray). Chest discomfort especially on left side, especially with deep inhale and when moving or laying on my side persisted.  Lungs felt better but still left side chest discomfort. Followed up with a chest CT after three weeks and it showed pericardial effusion and splenomegaly in addition to micro nodules in left lung. Pulmonologist cleared me for lung issues, infectious disease tested many things all came back negative. The source of the random chest pain especially on inhaling, shortness of breathe, etc has not been solidly determined and all symptoms started after getting the first moderna shot. After the second shot I felt extremely unwell with high fever for many days. Chest CT was done after the second shot so it is hard to know if the pericardial effusion and splenomegaly came from both shots.
PRIOR_VAX: MMR vaccine age 9, hives
ALLERGIES: Allergic to MMR vaccine as a child (hives)

After 3-4 minutes, client reported feeling dizzy and EMT1 observed that she was diaphoretic.  Client?s husband was standing next to her and held onto client.  EMT1 grabbed the zero-gravity chair and guided client from her existing chair into the zero-gravity chair.  At 1313 RN2 radioed Lead RN to go to vaccination station 7.  Lead RN arrived at the station at 1312.  Lead RN confirmed with client that she was still feeling a little dizzy, but was beginning to feel better.  EMT provided client with a bottle of water and client was periodically sipping the water.  Client stated that she had eaten and drank plenty prior to being vaccinated.  Client stated she has no known allergies.  Client reported having high blood pressure and epilepsy. EMT1 and EMT2 escorted client and client?s husband and friend to the observation room.  Prior to walking over, Lead RN explained to client she would need to be observed for 30 minutes.  At 1330 client was seated in observation room and vitals were taken by EMT2 (BP:  122/82, HR:  76, O2Sat:  99).  At 1345 EMT2 took client vitals again (BP:  126/82, HR:  82, O2Sat:  99). Lead RN educated client on normal vs adverse effects of the vaccine and to go to urgent care if she started to experience dizziness again. We report an event of transverse myelitis occurring one week after second dose of COVID vaccine in a seventy-five-year-old previously able-bodied gentleman with HTN and DM2. He developed a painless, distal greater than proximal, subacute onset weakness of the right greater than left upper and lower extremities with bowel and bladder retention. He was treated with methylprednisolone IV q24h for 3 days and IVIG (divided over 3 days). At one month from symptom onset, he was able to walk, but continued to have urinary and fecal retention. By 60 days since symptom onset, he had near resolution of symptoms.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: May 18 I received my first Covid Moderna Vaccination.  4 hours later when I went to urinate there was blood on the toilet paper. It only lasted about 3-4 minutes.  2 hours after that I went to the bathroom again to urinate and it burned really bad.  I called my doctor and was able to see her the next morning ( May 19)  She sent my urine in for a culture and it came back as a Urinary Tract Infection. She treated me with Cipro for 3 days. She felt that I should see my GYN regarding the bleeding and felt that it is Post Menopausal Bleeding. I saw my GYN on June 7. She did a Pap Smear and it came back normal but it showed that I have a Bacterial Vaginitis infection and treated me with Metronidazole Vaginal Gel for 5 days. Today June 14 is my last day for that. But when I went to the bathroom to urinate there was some blood again on the toilet paper. I don't know if all this is a coincidence or if this is a reaction to the vaccination. My doctor doesn't think it is a reaction but I want to make sure since I was fine till I was vaccinated. I am concerned because I had no sign of the bleeding or the burning before I got the vaccination. I am also concerned because my next vaccination is tomorrow June 15. If I don't get the second one then is the 1st one not going to be valid. If I do get the second one could I have a worse problem with bleeding and UTI? Due to the bleeding I have to have a vaginal ultrasound and depending on the results I might have to have an endometrial biopsy.
LAB_DATA: Urine Culture - positive Pap Smear - negative but showed Bacterial Vaginitis Vaginal Ultrasound - scheduled for June 21

The doctors examined him and ran blood tests, including a tox screen, but could find nothing wrong with him.  We followed up with his family doctor the following week and she found nothing wrong other than dehydration.   On 6/5/21, my son received his 2nd dose of the vaccine lot #ew0202. On 6/11/21, my son had a major seizure at home with convulsions, was unresponsive and had to be taken from our home by ambulance to the hospital.  The emergency room doctors performed a CT Scan and other tests and again could find no reason for the seizure.  My son has been healthy his entire life and has never experienced anything like this before.  My son is very active with travel soccer and in very good health.  I do not know if the vaccine was the cause of these two episodes  but it seems to be the only common thread

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Paraesthesia, in the form of prickling sensations on the skin, began one week after injection (04/25/2021). It occurred randomly and sporadically across my whole body, but most commonly in the legs. This symptom has continued (intermittently) up to the time of this reporting.  Roughly two weeks after injection (05/01/2021), intermittent muscle weakness and vertigo began. The muscle weakness was primarily in my legs and arms, on both sides, and created a sensation that the limbs were limp/floppy or that the hand/foot was unusually heavy. What I describe as vertigo was not dizziness or the perception of spinning, but rather a sensation of being off-balance or having an unsteady head. When present, the vertigo was triggered by motion of the head (e.g. the motions caused by walking). The muscle weakness is generally worse at night. The vertigo had ceased by 05/30; muscle weakness eventually became persistent, and continues up to the time of this reporting.  An additional symptom that eventually appeared is occasional tensing and soreness of various muscle groups in the legs and arms, as if they have been intensely exercised (but they have in fact not been exercised). This also continues up to the time of this reporting.  On the night of 05/14 through the morning of 05/15, I experienced exceptionally serious muscle weakness and vertigo. The vertigo made it nearly impossible to go to sleep, because the beginning of sleep would trigger a sensation of falling that would cause me to immediately awaken. In the morning, my calf muscles were so weak that it could be difficult to stand up for more than a few minutes at a time, and they would sometimes shake with the effort. These symptoms gradually improved over the course of the following day.  I had additional "attacks" on the night of 5/20 through the morning of 05/21, and the night of 05/29 through the morning of 05/30. Again, these led to serious leg weakness that improved gradually during the subsequent day. A persistent low level of leg muscle weakness eventually developed.  On 06/14 I began an attempted treatment with a 10-day prednisone course. Outcome still future and therefore unknown.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 1 week after shot. Sore chest muscles, ear ringing, severe anxiety, winded easily, racing heart, heart palpitations, fast pulse with minimal activity. Waking in night with rapid pulse 140BPM, resting pulse between 90-110.  Headache, severe muscle aches and night sweats.  These severe symptoms lasted two weeks. Symptoms slowly have been subsiding, but it took nearly two months. Still have a slightly elevated resting heart rate. Other than that, feel fully recovered. Very scary experience! Grateful to be vaccinated though.

Blood tests were normal: Sedimentation Rate Full Thyroid Panel Lipid profile with Insulin Markers CBC w/ differential Comprehensive Metabolic Vitamin D

SYMPTOM_TEXT: PARALYSIS ON LEFT SIDE; NO FEELING OR STRENGTH IN LEFT SIDE; BLOOD CLOT IN THE BRAIN; CONFUSION; SLURRED SPEECH; UNSTEADY WALKING; FEELS DIZZY; NO ENERGY FOR ANYTHING; AGITATION; LOSS OF HEARING IN LEFT EAR; This spontaneous report received from a patient and her husband and concerned a 45-year-old female patient. Initial information received on 07-JUN-2021 was processed together with additional information received via 2 telephone calls to and from the patient's husband on 11-JUN-2021. The patient's height and weight were not reported. No past medical history or concurrent conditions were reported. The patient had no family history of any blood/clotting disorders and that she did not travel anywhere prior to receiving the vaccine. The patient received COVID-19 vaccine Ad26.CoV2.S (suspension for injection, route of administration not reported, batch number unknown), dose not reported, administered once in total on 13-MAY-2021 for prophylactic vaccination. The batch number was not reported and has been requested. On an unspecified date, the patient experienced feeling dizzy, and had no energy for anything. On 14-MAY-2021, the patient started feeling confused, her mouth started feeling like it was drawing, and her speech started slurring. On 28-MAY-2021 she went to bed and got up and she couldn't feel her left side, with paralysis. She was also drooling and her husband took her to the hospital. The patient was flown by helicopter to another hospital. During the telephone call to the reporter, he reported that his wife's laboratory results were all within normal ranges at the second hospital, including her platelet count at 189,000 (units and normal range not reported). On 29-MAY-2021, a magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) scan of her brain revealed a 12 mm blood clot in the thalamus. The patient was treated with Aspirin (acetylsalicylic acid) and Plavix (clopidogrel bisulfate). It was reported that the clot could not be cleared before she was discharged after 4 days hospitalization on 31-MAY-2021.  As of 07-JUN-2021, the patient reported being highly agitated and could not hear out of her left ear, had no feeling or strength on her left side and was very unsteady walking. As of 11-JUN-2021, the patient's husband reported that the patient was still experiencing weakness of the left side of her body with no energy for anything (reported as being very active prior to vaccination), trouble walking, feeling dizzy sometimes, trouble hearing with her left ear, was very agitated and was frustrated that these events had happened to her. The patient was on medical leave from work at the time of reporting. The action taken with COVID-19 vaccine Ad26.CoV2.S was not applicable. The patient had not recovered from the events.  This report was serious (life-threatening, disability or permanent damage, caused/prolonged hospitalization and other medically important condition).; Sender's Comments: V0: This spontaneous report received from a patient and her husband concerned a 45-year-old woman who experienced blood clot in the thalamus 15 days after vaccine. No past medical history or concurrent conditions were reported. The patient had no family history of any blood/clotting disorders and that she did not travel anywhere prior to receiving the vaccine. On day 15, the patient went to bed and got up and she couldn't feel her left side, with paralysis. She was also drooling and her husband took her to the hospital. The patient was flown by helicopter to another hospital. During the telephone call to the reporter, he reported that his wife's laboratory results were all within normal ranges at the second hospital, including her platelet count at (189,000). On day 16, a magnetic resonance imaging (MRI) scan of her brain revealed a 12 mm blood clot in the thalamus. The patient was treated with aspirin and clopidogrel. It was reported that the clot could not be cleared before she was discharged after 4 days. As of day 25, the patient reported being highly agitated and could not hear out of her left ear, had no feeling or strength on her left side and was very unsteady walking. As of day 29, the patient's husband reported that the patient was still experiencing weakness of the left side of her body with no energy for anything, trouble walking, feeling dizzy sometimes, trouble hearing with her left ear, was very agitated and was frustrated that these events had happened to her. The patient was on medical leave from work at the time of reporting. The occurrence of blood clot in the thalamus could represent background incidence of such events in the general population and the normal platelet count exclude thrombosis with thrombocytopenia syndrome. However, a relationship with Janssen Covid-19 vaccine cannot be ruled out and thus the relationship is considered indeterminate.
