a 14 year old male with no significant past medical history who was in his usual state of health until he after his 2nd dose of Pfizer COVID-19 vaccination on Friday afternoon 6/11.  On Saturday 6/12 he had headache, fever in the AM and had poor oral intake during the day and in the afternoon had developed mid sternal chest pain that Described as thumping and wrapped around his chest under his arms.  He felt that it was worse with inspiration and continued to worsen despite tylenol.  He went to a medical center where his workup on Saturday evening 6/12 was normal (including EKG and blood work).  He also had some dizziness at that time but no syncope.  He was changed from as needed tylenol to as needed motrin and instructed to take famotidine.  On Sunday his chest pain persisted but was stable and he continued on motrin. On Monday 6/14 he had chest pain that felt like pounding this AM, headache, body aches, and pain in his bilateral arms, mouth and throat.  He had some nausea but no vomiting or diarrhea.  He represented to a medical center where his troponin was  0.25 ng/ml (normal 0-0.03 ng/ml)  pro-BNP  324 (normal 0-125 pg/ml); ESR 9; CK 359; CK-MB 20.3; WBC 3.9; Hgb 14.1; plts 181. And he was noted to have ST elevations on EKG.  He received toradol at 2:30pm with some improvement in his pain. SYMPTOM_TEXT: The day after I got my second dose, I went to the gym and afterwards I got really nauseated, and really tired. I went home and took a big nap that I felt like I couldn't wake up from. Then the next day ( Sunday) I got a really bad headache. Monday it got worse, that is when I took Tylenol. Tuesday I traveled, I got a huge migraine. When I arrived it got worse so I started taking Tylenol regularly. Thursday, I talked to my PCP through a Tele-health appt. My symptoms got worse, migraines, aches, nausea etc. They gave me some antibiotics to take for 10 days, and another one for 5 days, but they didn't help at all. Friday, I slept all day, I couldn't move, or even keep my head up. Late Friday night/Early Saturday morning, I got a stabbing pain in my neck. When I woke up officially the next day I felt a little better, but I continued to have a severe headache/migraine for about 2 weeks after that. I have now recovered from this.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Client received her Moderna Covid vaccine dose 2 lot #: 027C21A and expires 7/1/21 at approximately 1:05pm. PHN noticed client had mask down and asked client to cover her nose, since she was waiting for her mother to get medical consult.  Client then reports she "just feels really hot." PHN  observes client is alert and oriented x4 and reports no dizziness, no shortness of breath, no blurred vision, and no chest pain. At 1:15pm, vitals are: blood pressure: 160/100, heart rate:81 and unable to get oxygen saturation due to long acrylic nails. Client reports not taking any medications, no known allergies and only has history of rosacea. PHN  alert Lead PHN to come assist with client who is having a reaction. PHN  assesses client and observes flushed face and rash on upper back and front neck area.  Client reports to  that she feels "lightheaded", PHN  asks  RN to get gravity chair and switch client to gravity chair. Client able to transfer herself to anti-gravity chair by herself. PHN  offered client Benadryl and client accepted. Client reports she can get family to pick her up.  At 1:18pm,  PHN  provides client with oral Benadryl 50 mg.  Vitals are heart rate: 81 and blood pressure: 170/100. Client reports she feels "hot", her head "feels weird" and she feels like her "heart is racing."  RN assists by fanning client. RN takes over vitals blood pressure: 180/130 at 1:20pm and client reports feeling hot everywhere. While PHN  is assessing client PHN activates 911 at 1:23pm.  At 1:25pm, client reports she feels "throbbing in her head and chest", "heavy breathing", "lightheaded" and PHN  notes flushed face. Vitals are: Blood pressure:180/120 heart rate:86 and oxygen: 98%.  Fire department arrives at 1:29pm and assumes care.  At 1:34pm client was wheeled out of facility on gurney and was taken to hospital.

My adverse event is that I contracted Covid two months and one week after being fully vaccinated.   I received my first dose of Moderna on 3-20-21 and my second dose on 4-17-21, but I tested positive for Covid on June 9, 2021, after symptoms started on June 6, 2021.   I contacted Health Department to ask why I got infected when I was supposed to have 94% protection. I was concerned that a new variant may be circulating in our community.  She suggested that I report my experience via this form.  Additionally, I believe I contracted it from my 14 year old granddaughter, who was also fully vaccinated, but had just received her final dose of the Pfizer vaccine on June 4, 2021, from the same pharmacy where I was vaccinated months earlier, when she became ill and also tested positive for Covid on June 9th, 2021.  Just seems odd that in one household we'd have two "break through" events and we received our vaccinations from the same pharmacy.

Advised results may take 2 to 3 days for to be available, and all results will show up on medical records. We will call you with any positive results. Tylenol or ibuprofen as needed for fevers, body aches. Over-the-counter cough and cold medication as needed. SYMPTOM_TEXT: On Friday, May 14, 2021 started to have aches and flu-like symptoms. Then on Saturday, May 15, 2021. developed a migraine-like headache and chest pain along with worsening flu-like symptoms.  By midnight Sunday, May 16, 2021 awoke with 8-9 out of 10 chest pain, with copious amounts of vomiting, a 9 out of 10 headache, abdominal pain with a feeling of hot than freezing, shivering, unable to keep clear liquids down. No loose stools,  reported having a normal bowel movement. reported that since the vomiting started overnight the chest pain got no better but felt worse like an elephant was sitting on his chest. was taken to Hospital emergency department where he was originally treated, Tests performed were bloodwork including Troponin levels, EKG, Chest X-Rays, and CT scan. Per the Physician Assistant who initially saw stated that his EKG was abnormal than his Troponin level was elevated. Due to concerns withs history of Marfan Syndrome and the possibility of a torn aorta, increased Troponin, abnormal EKG the ED doctor wanted him helicoptered to Hospital's Cardiac Cath Lab to rule out a torn aorta. was helicoptered to  Hospital taken to the Cardiac Cath Lab ruling out a torn aorta. After IV fluid hydration and other treatment, was diagnosed with myocarditis. Upon discharge,  was placed on medication and to follow up with his PCP and cardiologist  on 6/25/21.
LAB_DATA: Chest CT scan, Chest X-Ray, Blood work and EKG
ALLERGIES: Lactose intolerance, Soy Allergy, Tree Nut Allergy.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: A few days after the shot, my arm was still in extreme pain.   I was noticing that my arm wasn't able to extend how it normally does .  I called my PCP and let them know about the pain, and mobility issues., I called a week after, and then two weeks later because I was getting concerned.    My PCP referred me to get an EMG.  After that, he referred me to someone else,   He evaluated my shoulder and gave me the diagnosis of  Adhesive capsulitis.  doctor  sent me for physical therapy  for 1 month 2x a week.  I had that appointment with  Dr on June 4th.   I return to see him Monday June 21st for a follow up to see if I have had any improvement .   I am in excruciating pain.  I have never had any issues with my arm/shoulder.  It was a nurse that gave me the injection, at the health department.  I did go to a CVS and got my 2nd dose of pfizer on 6/8/21 with no additional side effects.  I have been to a lot of doctors for this.  My pain doctor was in shock.  And no one seems to have ever heard of this being a lasting side effect.   I struggle dressing, putting my seatbelt on, I can extend or reach in certain directions.   Its not just because of the pain? I physically can extend after a certain angle.  I am very concerned about the next steps on seeing how my doctors can help me through this bizarre diagnosis.    Like I said, I've never had any issues with my shoulder

SYMPTOM_TEXT: I noticed on about 3/30 at about 5 PM, I started itching in the upper right chest area where I had had a mastectomy of the right breast. I scratched and thought it would relieve the itch, but it didn't. I looked and noticed there was a welt there. I put on a little cortisone cream, which helped for only about 10 minutes. Afterwards, the itching became more pronounced, so I took 1 Benadryl tablet. It eased the itch a little, so I put on a little more cortisone cream. It got rid of the itch for a little longer. About 2 hours later, the rash became hot to the touch. I took another Benadryl tablet and went to sleep. I woke up at about 4 AM on 3/31, and my legs, left arm, and ankle were itching. It had spread. I took off my bracelets, because they aggravated the itch. I contacted medical center and had an e-visit with on-duty ER doctor about midnight on 4/1. She wasn't sure if my symptoms were caused by the seafood I had eaten earlier or by the COVID vaccination. She recommended i stop eating seafood and that I follow up with my PCP and to make sure I answered every V-safe text I received. She prescribed a steroid cream and oral steroids. She prescribed a 6-day regimen of steroids. After that, my situation improved. The steroids worked and the itching stopped. She urged me to keep my appointment for the second COVID vaccination. Everything cleared up, but then a week later (before the second vaccination), the itching returned on my neck and left arm. Welts and pimples reappeared. The skin was hot to the touch in the affected area. Intermittently, the welts would go down, but the pimples would appear and that was when the itching was especially bad. After that happened, I contacted my PCP by email to update her and assure her I had followed all her recommendations. She had recommended that I see a dermatologist. I had an e-visit with a dermatologist named Dr./MD. I don't remember the exact date, but it was before I received the second COVID vaccination. Dr. wasn't sure if the situation was caused by the seafood or by the vaccination, though he leaned towards the condition being possibly caused by the vaccine. He told me to continue with the Benadryl and he made an appointment for me to see him in person on June 8. He examined me in person that day and said that it looked like it had a bite pattern. He said it wasn't bed bugs, but it was possibly caused by a spider bite. I spend a lot of time outside, and he told me that I could have once been bitten in the past and that the venom could have lain dormant before it manifested its symptoms. He prescribed me clobetascol topic cream and put me on a 12-day regimen of prednisone. This regimen relieved my symptoms within hours. The cream works well on contact. On April 18, I received the second COVID shot. After the second shot, I didn't have any major side effects other than fatigue and sore muscles around the injection site.

I initially had symptoms one would expect from the second dose, including chills, body aches, headache, insomnia, thirst, physical restlessness and fatigue.  They resolved within around 48 hours, after a really good night's sleep.  The issue I'm reporting is one that may or may not be connected.  I had been treated for inflammation in my hands and feet, for about two years, which had mostly resolved by December 2020.  My massage therapist told me I was ready to stop treatment and I wasn't taking anti-inflammatory medication.  I had not seen a rheumatologist because my blood work showed no evidence of an autoimmune condition.  Instead, I had been treating my symptoms through physical therapy, massage therapy and OTC anti-inflammatories, with two rounds of steroids.  Following my second Moderna dose, I noticed pain, stiffness and swelling returning to my hands, as well as discomfort in my feet, knees, shoulders and other areas.  The tendons (e.g. flexor tendons in fingers) and tissue are inflamed, not the joints.  At first, I assumed the return of symptoms was merely a coincidence, but over time I began to wonder if the return of inflammation was a response to my immune system being triggered by the second shot.  (I am very grateful for having the vaccine and would get it again, despite my daily physical discomfort.)  I finally discussed my symptoms with my primary care provide, at the beginning of May 2021.  He prescribed a six-day pack of steroids and daily Meloxicam 15-mg.  I have been getting orthopedic massages to treat my hands/arms, for which I have a prescription.  My symptoms were at their peak, during the month of May, once the steroids wore off and my inflammation returned.  There has been some improvement over the past week, specifically less pain and more flexibility in my fingers.  At times, in late May, the symptoms were severe enough that I couldn't braid my hair or pick up a plastic bag of garbage.  I also had difficulty grabbing doorknobs, holding a kitchen knife and completing other tasks that involved grasping or making a fist, because I had difficulty bending some of my fingers and some would briefly lock in a "trigger" position.  Although my symptoms have shown some improvement, over the past week, the condition is far from resolved.
LAB_DATA: Routine bloodwork, including Rheumatoid Factor and inflammation were normal (first week of May 2021) Physical and visual exams by Primary Care Provider and massage therapist
OTHER_MEDS: Mirena IUD, women's multi-vitamin, B12, Vitamin D
HISTORY: orthopedic inflammation first treated in January 2019 and mostly resolved by December 2020
ALLERGIES: adverse reactions to minocycline, sulfa and flagil allergy to grass

SYMPTOM_TEXT: On 5/2/21, 5/5 or 6/21, and 5/8/21 during my usual/normal active/fast walking I had extreme pain and tightness across my chest, with radiating pain from my breastbone through to my back and pain down my left arm to the point of either causing me to slow my steps or stop walking completely and sit down. After 5-10 minutes the pain subsided enough to allow me to continue walking at a slower pace until I reached my destination. At the same time and continuing I had "fluttering" in what seemed to be my heart but was never confirmed so perhaps it was my breathing. This fluttering would occur after exercise or exertion and eventually I called my doctor about it and was directed to the ER at Hospital. on 5/17/21. An EKG was done which showed irregularities from one done five weeks previously.   I was given a bed and a heart monitor was attached to me.  A troponin test was done showing 60, which was up from 20 five weeks previously.  I was told this most probably indicated a heart blockage.  An ultra sound on my legs and chest area were performed with no blood clots found.  A heart catheterization was done 5/18/21.  Instead of finding arterial blockage, a Spontaneous Coronary Artery Dissection (SCAD) event was identified. A CT scan was performed, looking for arrhythmia's with negative results. The heart monitor data was reviewed and my heart was working normally. A baby aspirin per day was prescribed. I was discharged on 5/20/21 and have no ongoing symptoms of the SCAD event. I have no personal or family history of cardiac issues. Furthermore, the fluttering sensation I was experiencing from 5/2/21 through approximately 5/23/21, which I termed a "heart flutter" never showed up on the heart monitor data from the hospital. A pulmonologist was consulted and found no irregularities. Note: I received my first dose on 3/30/21 at 2:30pm. I received my second dose on 4/28/21 at 12:30p. The heart pain described above began just 4 days after this.

Patient states she received shingrix vaccine at 1:46pm and then had labwork completed after. She was sitting in the car when she felt hot, flushed, itchy and slightly short of breath which prompted her to come back into clinic.   She feels slightly short of breath siting in exam chair. She feels itchy and a little lightheaded. She feels her HR is high. She  Patient declines difficulty swallowing or throat tightening. No hives, no rash at injection site. No swelling of mouth, lips, cheeks or elsewhere. Patient states she has had recent reaction to PEG (polyethylene glycol) in Moderna COVID-19. She is also concerned to be allergic to Poly-Sorbate 80, which she describes to be similar  "cousin" to PEG. After she received her shingrix vaccine, the patient looked it up to see it contains PolySorbate 80 and it does. Patient took 25 mg tab of benadryl at around 2:40pm. I took patients vitals at 2:50pm to be HR 93, SpO2% 97%, BP 176/96, Temp is 99.1 and RR is 18. I told patient I was going to discuss with Dr. and return to the exam room.   I spoke to Dr. and explained patient situation and vitals. She asks for patient to stay in exam room for 30 minutes for another reevaluation afterwards to see how she is after receiving benadryl 25 mg.   Re-examined patient at 3:30pm. She states her face isn't flushed. She is no longer short of breath or having much tingling in her face and arms. She states overall she is feeling better Vitals are HR is 83, SpO2% at 98%, BP 160/80 and RR is 16. Patient states she feel strong and safe enough to go home. I relayed that I'll update Dr.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: After receiving 2nd dose of the Pfizer Vaccine at 4:00 PM, patient was seated in the waiting area. At  exactly 4:05 PM, Patients boyfriend motioned to staff to respond to said patient and asked for water. When staff observed patient, on site RN was motioned over as well. There-in, patient was observed to be pale and sweaty, and she was seated but leaning against boyfriend for support. Upon being asked name,  patient stuttered trying to state first name and could only produce ("T" sound with lips) Patient could not speak full word. By this time, blood pressure cuff and Pulse-ox were brought to assess vitals. Blood pressure - 55/35 and Pulse was 49. Respiration was 20 breaths per minute and shallow. Upon observing blood pressure, ambulance was called. Ambulance responded within 5 minutes. During time waiting for ambulance, patient had improvement and was able to state name and location. Patient was given water, could not hold but with assistance from boyfriend, was able to drink through a straw. Upon ambulance arrival, care was transferred and was transported to local hospital.

I received my first dose 05/25/2021. On my vaccination card, the administered nurse wrote for me to come back 06/15/2021 for my second dose. So I did today and got it done. Within few minutes of getting it administered, I developed a rash on my left arm (injection site), my heart began to beat rapidly, & I was experiencing shortness of breathe. They asked me to stay an additional 15-30 minutes and so I did until I felt a little better to leave.  I called my sister, considering we received our first dose on the same day but different place and she questioned why I got mines early and I explained that?s what my card said.  We hung up and I did some additional research, went on the CDC website and saw I was to get my second dose 28 days from my first dose and today made 21 days!   Same administrator the first time gave me my second dose today. She failed to correctly time my dose and didn?t not double check it was correct.  I never knew about the timing until today and as a healthcare professional, she should have known considering she would have been properly trained and now I?m experiencing difficulty breathing, chest pains, & heart beat feels off!
LAB_DATA: None yet. Following up with my doctor tomorrow

Patient got her COVID vaccine on April 22. This was the Moderna vaccine. About 4 days after the shot, she was still having a lot of arm soreness, some numbness and tingling, which goes down through the arm and into the whole hand. Feels always like she has just slept on the arm. She is having some difficulty lifting the arm and can only get it to about just above 90 degrees. Otherwise, she feels well. There has not been any redness, fever, or sign of infection. Left upper extremity: On exam she is quite tender in several places on the arm, primarily along the trapezius on her left side down along the supraspinous at the AC joint. Some of the deltoid bursa does lay very tender anteriorly and posteriorly over the shoulder joint. I am able to lift the arm, but she is very resistant to going up above that 90-degree point. Her internal-external rotation were good when she had the arm resting at her side, but she really was not able to do  any of that when she would try to lift the arm. Arm soreness with some limitation of motion. We will send a CBC, sedimentation rate, and CRP to make sure there is not any infection in the arm joint. Certainly, clinically that seems  quite, unlikely. I suspect this is just a prolonged reaction to the vaccine. She may be getting set up for a frozen shoulder, so if her lab work looks good. we will refer her for some physical therapy. While technically it is probably still fine to repeat the 2nd dose of the vaccine, I am not sure I can in good faith recommend that she do that, so I will discuss that with her as soon as her lab work is available.
HISTORY: Hypertension , hyperlipidemia, Anxiety , Seborrheic dermatitis at scalp

Received my Vaccine, felt well, came home.  Few hours later, felt tightness in chest and breathing was tight- but not too bad. Went to bed. Woke up writhing in agony. The most extreme bone and joint pain I have ever had in my life. I could not stand up straight or walk straight. My vision was blurred. I am a grown Woman and I literally cried that night.  Fever was 101.8. I took 5 Tylenol , one at a time with gatorade, between 11 pm and 6 am that morning , and only after the 5th was the pain reduced enough so that I could sleep.  The next day was the same, extreme pain, 101.+ fever and after trying to walk and have some coffee,  I fainted. My roomate helped me back to bed and i dont remember much from this point. Roomate nearly took me to ER. At one point, I didn't recognize my own pets. It was a blur.  This continued until sunday night when my fever finally began to come down and the pain decreased substantially.  As of today, I have stiffness and some mild pain in my joints, no fever, but I have fainted 3 separate times- meaning I could not stand up or sit up and fell. During this sound became very loud and light very bright. But resolving with rest.  I have a mild cough, some ear pressure, but no dizziness or phlegm. I cannot check my blood pressure at home, but it feels low. I nornally have low pressure but do not faint for no reason.  I remain on bed rest and take electrolyte drinks like Gatorade. Lots of water. Good appetite. Good diet. Really wish I knew what was happening. It is scary.  I am fit, active, no drugs or drinking ever.  I was very happy to receive my vaccines, but this has been a very scary experience for me. Thank You.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: A post I made where someone suggested I report this.   I know I was all for the vaccine but lemme share my experience: I got my second Vaccine June 4th.  Felt like dog. Exactly 7 days after (typical incubation period)  not only did I get the worst cold I've ever had I couldn't read, couldn't speak clearly and couldn't think. Just now at 5pm did I regain my ability to communicate fully.  This could have been from MS and the temperature change, the neurological part at least.  But I really do wanna warn people that something isn't legit with this vaccine.  I called the clinic several times and was blown off.  This isnt a normal or average reaction.  Please make your choices with caution.  Every case is different but this was my reaction.
CUR_ILL: None aside from a slight immediate reaction on 6/4 after initial second dose

SYMPTOM_TEXT: The first shot threw her out of remission and into an IBD (Crohns) flare with liquid stool about one week after the shot and visible blood in her stool for a week. The second shot caused a fever of 102.5 for about 12 hours and tiredness the next day as well as throwing her into a worse flare where she had liquid stools at least 4 days with visible blood two days after the vaccination. We are still dealing with the flare, so I do not know how long it will last or if she will need steroids to get her back into remission.

Seizures; Bood clots; Stuggling to breathe; Struggling to walk; ARDS; Acute hypoxic respiratory failure; Acute exacerbation of heart failure and sepsis; Acute exacerbation of heart failure and sepsis; Cardiac arrest; Blood infection; Fever; This spontaneous case was reported by a patient family member or friend (subsequently medically confirmed) and describes the occurrence of ACUTE RESPIRATORY DISTRESS SYNDROME (ARDS), ACUTE RESPIRATORY FAILURE (Acute hypoxic respiratory failure), SEPSIS (Acute exacerbation of heart failure and sepsis), CARDIAC FAILURE ACUTE (Acute exacerbation of heart failure and sepsis), CARDIAC ARREST (Cardiac arrest), SEIZURE (Seizures), THROMBOSIS (Bood clots), DYSPNOEA (Stuggling to breathe) and GAIT DISTURBANCE (Struggling to walk) in a 53-year-old male patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) for COVID-19 vaccination. The occurrence of additional non-serious events is detailed below.     Concurrent medical conditions included Obesity.   On 16-Apr-2021, the patient received first dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) 1 dosage form. On 15-May-2021 at 2:00 PM, received second dose of mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular) dosage was changed to 1 dosage form. On 15-May-2021, the patient experienced ACUTE RESPIRATORY DISTRESS SYNDROME (ARDS) (seriousness criteria death and medically significant), ACUTE RESPIRATORY FAILURE (Acute hypoxic respiratory failure) (seriousness criteria death and medically significant), DYSPNOEA (Stuggling to breathe) (seriousness criterion hospitalization prolonged) and GAIT DISTURBANCE (Struggling to walk) (seriousness criterion hospitalization prolonged). In May 2021, the patient experienced SEPSIS (Acute exacerbation of heart failure and sepsis) (seriousness criteria death and medically significant), CARDIAC FAILURE ACUTE (Acute exacerbation of heart failure and sepsis) (seriousness criteria death and medically significant), CARDIAC ARREST (Cardiac arrest) (seriousness criteria death and medically significant), INFECTION (Blood infection) and PYREXIA (Fever). On 17-May-2021, the patient experienced SEIZURE (Seizures) (seriousness criteria hospitalization prolonged and medically significant) and THROMBOSIS (Bood clots) (seriousness criteria hospitalization prolonged and medically significant). The patient was hospitalized from 15-May-2021 to 25-May-2021 due to DYSPNOEA, GAIT DISTURBANCE, SEIZURE and THROMBOSIS. The patient died on 25-May-2021. The reported cause of death was Cardiac arrest, Acute hypoxic respiratory failure, ards and acute exacerbation of heart failure and sepsis. It is unknown if an autopsy was performed. At the time of death, SEIZURE (Seizures), THROMBOSIS (Bood clots), DYSPNOEA (Stuggling to breathe), GAIT DISTURBANCE (Struggling to walk), INFECTION (Blood infection) and PYREXIA (Fever) outcome was unknown.      DIAGNOSTIC RESULTS (normal ranges are provided in parenthesis if available): On 15-May-2021, Blood pressure measurement: elevated (High) Twice normal. On 15-May-2021, Glycosylated haemoglobin: elevated (High) High. On 15-May-2021, Oxygen saturation: low (Low) Required intubation and was placed on ventilator.. On 15-May-2021, SARS-CoV-2 antibody test: negative (Negative) 1 negative COVID antibody test. On 15-May-2021, SARS-CoV-2 test: negatie (Negative) 3 negative COVID antigen tests.         No concomitant medications were provided.  It was reported that within few hours after second dose of vaccine patient was struggling to walk and to breathe. The reporter and her husband went to see the patient and took him to an emergency room (ER). In the ER his blood pressure was markedly elevated (twice normal) and his oxygen level was low and by midnight he required intubation and was placed on a ventilator. His HbgA1c was noted to be elevated. Two days after admission (17-May-2021), he developed seizures which the medical team believed to be due to blood clots and he was anti-coagulated. It was determined that he did not have blood clots on his heart valves as the source of the clots. The source of the blood clots was never identified. He later developed fever and was diagnosed with a blood infection and treated with antibiotics. At one point his oxygen requirement on the ventilator went down to 65% but later returned and remained at 100%. He ultimately died on 25-May-2021 and as per copy of his death certificate he had 4 causes of death as cardiac arrest, acute hypoxic respiratory failure, acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS) and acute exacerbation of heart failure and sepsis.  Treatment included, anticoagulants, antibiotics, intubation and ventilator.  Very limited information regarding these events has been provided at this time.  Further information has been requested.   This case was linked to MOD-2021-219410 (Patient Link).; Sender's Comments: Very limited information regarding these events has been provided at this time. With the second dose, the caller confirms she did get muscle stiffness and soreness in her left arm that goes up into her neck, but she did not have the tingliness. She had the same symptoms again in the arm she received the vaccine in except she didn't have tingliness, just the stiffness. It was definitely a lighter reaction that it was initially. Relapse of bipolar depression; Aches and pains; Ringing in her ears; Joint pain / Burning pains in her small joints; Myalgia; This literature case was received on 07-Jun-2021 and concerned a 49-year-old, female patient.  The patient's concurrent conditions included well controlled bipolar depression and comorbid attention-deficit / hyperactivity disorder. The patient's concomitant medications included buspirone, lurasidone, oxcarbazepine and trazodone, all for bipolar depression and lisdexamfetamine for comorbid attention-deficit / hyperactivity disorder.  On an unspecified date, two weeks earlier, the patient's depression was in full remission and she had scored 0 on the 9-item Patient Health Questionnaire (PHQ-9).   On an unknown date, a week before coming to clinic, the patient was vaccinated with influenza virus vaccine polyvalent (brand not specified; dose, route of administration, indication and anatomical location: not reported). The batch number was not reported.   On the same day, within a couple of hours after receiving influenza virus vaccine polyvalent, the patient started feeling depressed and became tearful. These symptoms were followed a couple of days later with aches and pains, which escalated over the subsequent days. She complained of joint pain, burning pains in her small joints and myalgia, and rated her pain as 6/10.   On an unspecified date, two weeks after her clinic visit, the patient returned to the clinic for an urgent, unscheduled visit due to escalating depression, which was rated as 18/27 on the PHQ-9 (a score of 15-19 was considered moderately severe). The patient also noticed ringing in her ears for the previous two days. On the assumption that patient's relapse of depression was related to an immune response, physicians agreed to a trial of celecoxib at dose of 200 mg twice a day and she was asked to return in a week if her condition did not improve.   On an unknown date, the patient started treatment with celecoxib for relapse of bipolar depression.   On an unknown date, the patient's depression resolved when treated with celecoxib.  On an unknown date, eight weeks later, the patient returned to clinic for a previously scheduled appointment and reported having experienced a dramatic response to celecoxib. Her depression had remitted rapidly, and she scored 0/27 on the PHQ-9. The patient reported an additional benefit of improved interpersonal interactions.   The outcome of 'pain', joint pain and myalgia was not reported.   The author assessed the event of bipolar depression as related to influenza virus vaccine polyvalent, while the causality for other events was not provided. Physicians discussed the possibility that patient's depression might be a reaction to the flu vaccine. On the assumption that her relapse of depression was related to an immune response they agreed to a trial of celecoxib. Should bipolar patients experience vaccination-induced relapse of depression, adding celecoxib to their treatment regimen could be helpful.  The event of bipolar depression was considered to be medically significant by a Physician within Seqirus' Pharmacovigilance and Risk Management Department. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Last May 6, 2021, I recieved my 1st dose of MODERNA vaccine. For the last 5 days I don't feel any side effects on my body. But on the 6th day after my vaccination, I started to feel anxiety, insomnia, brain fog followed by  depression, panic attack and rapid heart palpitation and it lasted for 3 weeks. Until now, there are times that I can still feel the rapid heart palpitation.
Tinnitus

May 22nd felt like I was going to have a heart attack.  Pain started in chest more throughout the next few days. May 26 went to health clinic. Was told to go to hospital. Had ekgs. One abnormal...was sent home with no treatment.  Was called but hospital nurse to come back in the next day to check for heart inflammation as she had recently read about the reverse effects with moderna. Had more ekgs done and never had a test for inflammation and got sent home. May 30th had headaches, muscle aches, sore throat at night and cough. Still having chest pain. Started getting a rash on my left side of my face.  May 31st, vomited and felt sick most of the day.  June 1st noon. Took a bath and got extremely dizzy and fatigued so I layed down. Didn't wake up till 7pm. June 2nd, had an appt with regular dr. Asked for a test to check for inflammation. Was told to take aleve 2 times a day.. Found out I'm allergic to it.. Had an echo done next morning. Was told test results were normal.  May 11th till present day, June 16th, I am struggling with breathing and still have chest pain. Given no treatment.

Few days after receiving the vaccine around 4/25, my mother complained to me that she was feeling very weak and tired, she was unable to hold anything down. She also had a rash. She became weaker and weaker so suddenly and unable to even drink protein drinks.  She finally went to the ER on 5/4 because she could barely walk, unable to eat anything and was short of breath.  They diagnosed her with pneumonia and a possible lung mass. She was diagnosed simultaneously 10 days later with small cell lung cancer however she had no symptoms prior. She received first dose chemo on 5/20/21 and had a reaction to the chemo that the doctor stated was very rare. They then had to try a different type of chemo for second dose 2 days later. She progressively got worse suddenly after chemo dose #3 and was in renal failure the day following chemo completion. She died on 5/27/2021. Her primary death diagnosis was sepsis, pneumonia and small cell lung cancer. I am reporting this for my mother because the vaccine has not been tested on cancer or chemo patients. It can and should not be regarded as coincidental. It needs to be tracked in case there are future reports regarding cancer patients.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: About two weeks after getting my first shot, besides the typical pain at the injection site ( felt like a decent punch to the arm for about 1 week), I had the sensation of having an abscessed tooth. I?ve had an abscessed tooth before and the sensation was the same. Both sides of my jaw were very sore, hard to open my mouth,  pain radiating up my jaw and into my ears on both sides of my face. The next day my face muscles ?dropped? like they became too relaxed and it seemed to me exactly like my abscessed tooth from the past. I had started to take some antibiotics that I have on hand in preparation for a visit to the oral surgeon. Three days of this and the pain and my muscle issue disappeared. I should note that I lost my taste throughout the three days that this happened. Everything is normal since, just wanted to bring this up and report this strange reaction.

Patient found to have tachycardia and hypertension.  CXR with pleural effusion, renal US with medical renal disease.  Worsening renal function and concern for hyper coagulable state with worsening D-Dimer and possible pulmonary embolus but unable to obtain contrast images due to renal failure.    6/15 - transferred to ICU for heparin drip for worsening D-dimer.  Nephrology, rheumatology and infectious disease consulted.  Continued chest pain, cough with hemoptysis.  Remains afebrile and otherwise hemodynamically stable.  Started on ceftriaxone empirically.  Concern for MIS-C, vaccine related adverse event vs autoimmune vasculitis.

Blood culture - no growth to date.  Urinalysis - 200 protein, large occult blood, 82 RBC, 9 WBC, trace bacteria.  6/15 - Chest CT w/o contrast - Mixed pulmonary opacities, nonspecific.  Consider vasculitis, septic emboli, fugal infection or zoonotic pneumonia.  6/15 - echocardiogram - trace pericardial effusion. *COVID-19 Vaccine dose #2 was given on 4/16/21 **TDAP booster was given on 3/10/21  I had no side effects after any of the vaccinations. I had a bit of a sore arm after the TDAP and the first COVID-19 vaccination but that was it. I didn't even have a sore arm really at all after the second COVID-19 shot. I did have a bandaid mark that lingered for a few days after the second COVID-19 shot but that was it.  I was 30 weeks and 6 days pregnant during the first COVID-19 shot. I felt the baby kicking normally after that and had normal follow up appointments after that too. My entire pregnancy was completely normal (this was my first pregnancy) with no complications or issues. I felt great throughout the entire pregnancy and was active biking, working out, walking, etc. I would consider myself a very healthy and active person and I followed all of the pregnancy "guidelines" in terms of what to eat, what not to eat, etc.  The adverse event here is the fact that my baby was stillborn at 39 weeks and 4 days. The appointment with the doctor the week before was totally normal too. What the doctor *thinks* happened is that my amniotic fluid somehow disappeared in the final few days before going into labor (they don't know where it went - my water did not break prior to the delivery of the baby) and the lack of fluid caused the baby to pass meconium. The high level of meconium surrounding her and the amount of time she was exposed to it seem to have degraded the umbilical cord, affecting her oxygen flow. By the time I went into labor, she may have already been dead, though I did not know it. When I got to the hospital in labor, there was already no heartbeat.  Baby delivery date: 5/26/21 Weight: 6 lbs 9 oz Length: 21 in  The mystery here is why was there suddenly a lack of fluid and why did that cause her to pass so much meconium? The doctors do not know and there does not seem to be a way to share this information with other doctors or facilities to gain a better understanding.
LAB_DATA: Autopsy of the baby Blood tests of both parents

So the day I go the shot, I got a fever of about 101, I took Tylenol so it didn't last super long. I went home and went to bed and probably slept about 14 hours. The next day I had a fever again and got extremely nauseas, I was also very very tired. I had nausea for about a week and the fever subsided after about a day. When that finally went away, three weeks later I started to get a severe pain in my right buttocks area that was excruciating. I took medicine thinking it would go away and then I started getting a rash and the pain was all underneath that rash. I went to the DR and he said it was 100% shingles but fit the description so he treated me for that and it lasted about two weeks more. He gave me gabapentin to help with the pain. It was considered a mild outbreak of shingles. A couple weeks later my face swelled up on the left side. I went to my dentist and found out that my body was rejecting one of my teeth, I had to be treated for an infection in my mouth and then do a temporary bridge.
LAB_DATA: Dental xray showed tooth problem but did not have any labs or anything

Patient experienced usual arm soreness from the shot, but as the days wore on, the soreness progressed into pain. Within a few days, patient realized the pain was more than a usual vaccination soreness. Within 7 days, Patient's shoulder was making loud popping sounds, and he kept feeling like it was falling out of socket. Basic movements like combing hair, teeth brushing, driving, and typing were painful and difficult with his left arm. Patient visited a physical therapist, and he said it isn't rotator cuff, but it could be a laberal tear. An MRI would better diagnose the issue. The physical therapist recommended 6 weeks of immobility on his shoulder. Patient purchased a brace and is wearing that to prevent mobility. Patient had not done anything else to injure his shoulder and was perfectly healthy when he presented himself to be vaccinated.
LAB_DATA: Patient's physical therapist performed a physical examination on 6/7/2021. No other tests or labs have been performed. An MRI is recommended, but hasn't been scheduled due to the high cost of an MRI.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Within 24 hours of the first dose of Moderna COVID-19 vaccine I developed a meibomian gland infection and injected conjunctiva in my  right eye.  This resolved within 5 days.  Within 24 hours of receipt of the second dose of Moderna vaccine I developed identical signs and symptoms in my right eye as well as a stye in my left eye and massive lymphadenopathy and swelling in my left axilla (the arm of vaccine administration for both vaccinations).  The eye conditions resolved within 10 days.  However, the lymphadenoapthy persisted for at least 4 months, with moderate resolution.  I continue to have some painless swelling in my left axilla.
LAB_DATA: Examination by an ophthalmologist who conducted a viral PCR test of conjunctival fluid (negative) and tests for COVID-19 associated antibodies in conjunctival fluid (results unknown).

Rapid onset vision loss in left eye with concurrent rapid onset high blood pressure and rapid pulse.  Testing showed existing crowded optic nerve (previously undiagnosed), swelling of the optic nerve, delayed blood flow to optic nerve, and leakage around optic nerve head.  Vision loss progressed over about five days, stabilized, and may now be somewhat improved.  Diagnosis is Non-Arteric Ischemic Optic Neuritis (NAION), for which there is no treatment and uncertain prognosis.  Some extent of permanent vision loss tis epected.  Concurrent rapid onset of hypertension (systolic 150s-170s; diastolic low 100s at times) and fluctuating rapid pulse (80s-110). Currently being treated for hypertension but not yet fully controlled.  Blood tests revealed elevated inflammatory markers (high C-reactive protein and sedimentation rate and positive ANA.  Follow-up tests to determine cause of hypertension are underway.  Thus far, no heart abnormalities, no carotid artery blockage, and negative for a number of autoimmune disorders and other possible causes.  Prior to this event, blood pressure and pulse were normal and eye exams showed no vision or retina problems, glaucoma, or macular degeneration.  Cardiologist and rheumatologist have not ruled out inflammatory response to Covid vaccine, have encouraged reporting of this event to VAERS, and have advised against taking any other Covid booster.   Note that the optometrist who first saw me when the vision loss began has since told me that he saw only two cases of NAION in 38 years of practice before mine, but has seen two more besides me in the last couple of months.  Both were patients of similar age with similar rapid onset of vision loss, and both had taken the Covid vaccine about four weeks before.
LAB_DATA: MRI (4/17/2021) - Increased restricted diffusion in left optic nerve with mild increased T2 signal.  No intracranial hemorrhage, mass lesions or vascular territory. parenchymal infarct seen;  Optic Nerve Scan (4/19/2021) - Abnormal thinkness and elevation of OS > OD but no vessel obscuration in fundus.   Antinuclear Antibodies (ANA) w/Reflex (4/21/2021) - Positive.  CRP High Sensitive (4/21/2021) - 13.80 mg/l.   Sedimentation Rate (4/21/2021) - 4.3 mm/hr.   Humphrey Visual Field (4/22/2021) - Left Eye Field is reliable; finding include cecocentral scotoma, inferior altitudinal; mean deviation is -9.18.   Fluorescein Angiography (4/22/2021) - OD - normal arterial and venous filing with mid-late leakage at nasal and temporal edges of optic disc; OS - normal arterial filling but slightly delayed superior temp venous filling as compared to inf temp - with mid-late leakage with optic nerve head, especially inferotemporally .   Color Fundus Photography (4/22/2021) - disc findings include edema; macula findings include normal observations; vessel findings include tortuous vessels; periphery findings include normal observations.   US Renal Artery Doppler (5/5/21) - estimated 60% blockage in left renal artery.   US Carotid Complete (5/28/2021) - No significant narrowing of carotid arteries.   EKG (6/9/2021) - Normal EKG.   All other blood tests (Lyme Disease, ANA by IF, Syphilis Antibody, Rheumatoid Factor Screen, Renin Activity, Aldosterone, ACTH, metabolic markers, CBC values, and Hemoglobin A1C completed during this period were in negative/normal.  Cholesterol was slightly elevated.    Prior to this event, I was very healthy for my age and had no history of vision problems, hypertension, rapid pulse, or high inflammatory markers.  Something set off a very rapid onset of hypertension and vision loss, and so far, no underlying cause has been identified.  I am thankful that the Covid vaccine was available to me--and would take it again in same circumstances--but I do feel that the second does did cause an inflammatory response, increasing my blood pressure and causing the swelling blood flow problems in the eye that led to my loss of vision.  It is important that my case be considered by CDC in assessing overall safety of mRNA vaccines so that future patients can be appropriately informed of potential risks.
PRIOR_VAX: Shingrix first shot (November  2019) - inflammation at injection site (Dr. advises now against 2nd dose)

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Post COVID-19 vaccine reaction. Patient felt pressured by her work to get the vaccine for COVID-19 and on Thursday, 27 May 2021, patient decided to get the vaccine. She went to a mass vaccination site and within 5 minutes of receiving patient started to "feel weird." She reports that will in the observation line her throat felt heavy, so that talking was fatiguing. While in the observation line they checked her blood pressure and respiration. Per her report, her BP norm, breathing not restricted. It was recommended that she call EMS to have Benadryl administered. Patient declined at this point and decided to do this herself. Patient decided to drive herself to the ER. As I drove the numbness spread to behind my eyes, under cheek bones, jaw, back third of tongue, arms and joints including wrists and knees. Small turns along the way in the car would shift my proprioception and cause nausea, my response time was slower. I decided to stop by my house, get an ER go bag and then head to ER. By the time I got to ER I felt numbness in the back of my head and at base cervical spine worsened by rotation. As well as lower spine, non muscular. Getting out of the car I realized my walking was extremely slow, despite my best attempts to walk at a regular speed, it felt like walking in a pool. I checked in and told them mild anaphylaxis. I know they have a lot of people coming in and saying they have had a bad reaction to the vaccine when their arm hurts or they have mild cold symptoms, I didn?t have time to be perceived that way because I could feel my cognition changing rapidly. I realized talking with the check in lady that my ability to talk had changed, my cognition was significantly slower than half speed of normal and I was having word finding issues leaving me with simple sentences taking up to 20 seconds. In the car while using voice dictation to update my mom I remember the heaviness in my throat was getting worse making swallowing challenging. I was checked in pretty quickly. I knew what I wanted to say but the delivery was hard, I felt sabotaged neurally. They brought me right back. Attending ER doc was not phased in the slighted. Blood test panel looked normal, I sat in the ER chair there for two hours. I wonder if they just decided to wait it out. He ultimately came to me and said that I was probably fine, that everything looked normal that he could check. He asked me to walk for him and I needed to grasp his hand so hard just to get up, and then proceed to barely take steps because of how slow and off balance I was. He told me I?m likely allergic to the vaccine, he?s not seen a response like mine. That I should go home and wait it out. And that they have no treatment plan for adverse reactions at this time. I asked if Benadryl or some type of antihistamine was was wise and he dismissed the idea, I was surprised by that. When I left I felt a little better when I left in terms of numbness but was very slow getting out to the car. Since then I have had the numbness return in waves. I went to work the following day, made myself. It was hard, I started to notice things like processing the laundry in the back room, completely overwhelming me eye-to-brain, the laundry visually looked so busy and overwhelming, I had to leave the room due to a small surge in nausea x vertigo type of feeling. Looking at my computer screen and charting elicited the same response, to a lesser degree. I got home and it became much worse throughout the evening. I ended up cancelling my Friday, I know you know that?s a big deal for me.  Since then I have lost my appetite, have been sleeping from 11pm-1pm (since Friday, so two days in a row now). When I look around with my eyes this affects the proprioception and dizziness. I?m still pretty slow and weak. My parents took my laundry yesterday knowing I couldn?t do it. I cleaned my kitchen and showered and ended up paying for it the rest of the day with jaw joint numbness (made worse by chewing, does help with the appetite problem, as I eat I get neurally tired in my jaw with the numbness and just don't want to continue) and behind eye numbness returning as well as feeling like my head is on a slow off-kilter rotation around C1 like a slow motion bobble head (vertigo?). I?m also not emotionally myself and even had an argument with my parents which is unusual these days (I'm glad I can say that). After they left not an hour later, their visit started to fade so drastically in my memory I wasn?t sure how long they were here and even started to notice missing prices or gaps in memory of what happened while they were here (they were there for around two hrs).
LAB_DATA: CBC with differential ESR CMP TSH with free T3 and free T4 GM1 IgM Autoantibodies GM1 IgG Autoantibodies CK total + isoenzymes

On May 25, 8 days after my 2nd pfizer dose, i noticed a small rash on my chest (I thought it was actually a cluster of mosquito bites at first). I didn't think much of it.  At the time of my 2nd dose of pfizer, i was 27 weeks pregnant. The rash appeared on my chest at 28 weeks pregnant. 11 days after my 2nd pfizer dose and 3 days after the small rash appeared on my chest, on May 28, 2021, i went to an obgyn appointment and received 2 more vaccines: a RhoGAM shot in my butt (I have type O- blood) and a Tdap vaccine in my left arm -- both routine shots to get at 28 weeks of pregnancy. 3 days after those shots were administered, on May 31, a rash appeared on my right upper arm area. By June 2nd (16 days after 2nd pfizer and 5 days after tdap and rhogam) the rash on my arm and chest intensified, and i had bumps and rash forming in small patches on my stomach, legs, and neck/jawline. The rash was extremely itchy and uncomfortable. It seemed to spread very rapidly if it was touched. It looked like bug bites at first but would quickly spread into larger patches. I was unable to do regular things like exercise and wear regular clothes or use my regular products on my skin. On June 3rd I saw a dermatologist who prescribed me an antihistimine pill and a steroid cream,, and who said it might have just been a rash that happens sometimes to pregnant women, but perhaps the vaccines were involved. She said the rash could be "Atopic Eruption of Pregnancy (AEP)." I also saw my obgyn on June 7, and she also took a look at the rash. With the help of the steroid cream and the antihistimine pill, the rash stopped spreading by June 8 and stopped icthing and irritating me by June 11. It is now June 16 and the rash is starting to fade. I am now 31 weeks pregnant.

As a result, I was kept up all night from the pain. Hours later I began sweating and feeling feverish with a headache. Out of everything, the pain throughout my entire body was the worst thing next to the headache. Pain was an eight out of ten. I also had sporadic hot flashes along with inner ear pain. It wasn?t until June 11, 2021, that I felt the pain in my joints and muscles had subsided. Treatment included: Tylenol, Excedrin, Pain Relief Medication  On Monday, June 14, 2021, exactly one week from vaccination, I awoke with really bad vertigo, inner ear pain, nausea, and sporadic hot flashes. I had a headache instantly after receiving the vaccine. At 03:00AM, on 04/04, I woke up and started vomiting for the next 3 hours. I was able to stop enough to get my children up and then I started to vomit again. I took some anti-nausea medication (promethazine and Ondansetron) it helped a little, but I kept throwing it back up. My children called 911 and they sent an ambulance for me. They gave me another ondansetron, but I had used a suppository. They took me to a ER. While at the ER they performed a lot of tests. There was an abdominal CT, transvaginal ultrasound because of the stomach pain, I had an EKG and a lot of blood work. They gave me medication for my migraine and I was given an IV. I also received something for the pain in my stomach, but I don't recall what it was. I was given enough medication to where I could finally get a little rest. The results that they came back with was that there was free fluid in my belly, there were spots on the scans around my ovaries and uterus and there was a lot of swelling in my intestines and stomach. I was referred to a couple other different doctors. Six months prior to receiving the vaccine, I went into septic shock and my heart briefly stopped. There was a lot of damage to different systems of my body after that happened. The doctors were not sure what kind of reaction I had. They weren't sure if it was a coincidence with what I already had going on, or if it was the vaccine. I also had a false positive pregnancy test and if I test, it still shows positive. They drew blood to verify that I was not pregnant. I went to an OBGYN and now I need to go to an gastroenterologist. I also followed up with my PCP.
LAB_DATA: I had an abdominal CT, a transvaginal ultrasound, an EKG and blood work.

Patient received the 1st COVID vaccine Pfizer Lot#EW0185 on 05/22/21 at 11:18AM. The patient presents to the vaccination site today for her 2nd COVID Pfizer vaccine with her mother. She alerted RN that she developed dizziness 24 hours following her 1st vaccine. RN alerted RN lead who responded. The patient told RN the dizziness lasted about one hour. She did eat prior to receiving the vaccine on 05/22/21. The patient did eat today prior to presenting to the vaccination site. The patient did not report SOB after the 1st dose of COVID vaccine Pfizer. The patient did not consume any medications for the reactions to the 1st dose. They did not follow up with any medical care providers after developing dizziness. The patient denies any chronic conditions, or current medications. The patient has no known allergies. RN consulted with the Medical Consult Team regarding the patient and her reactions to the first dose of COVID vaccine Pfizer. Approval was received from PHN via text message. RN provided education regarding s/s of anaphylaxis, to report any symptoms during observation to EMT, to follow up with PCP if the patient develops any symptoms post vaccination, to consume water prior to vaccination and after, and V-safe. The patient was also instructed to wait 30 minutes in the observation period. The patient and her mother voiced understanding of this. The patient stated she had already drank water while waiting in line pending vaccination. Patient received the 2nd COVID vaccine Pfizer Lot#EW0187 on 06/12/21 at 12:44PM. The patient waited in the observation area for 30 minutes with her mother. She did not alert the EMTs of any symptoms during her observation period.

Immediately after the shot (10:29 am) , the patient's arm developed a round, swollen area around the injection site that turned into a hard knot. Within 5 minutes, the patient described feeling hot, dizzy, experiencing an elevated heart rate, and her arm was hurting (10:34 am). Over the next 10-20 minutes her symptoms did not improve, but she began to feel light-headed and stated multiple times that she may pass out; She also described having a dry mouth and tingling sensations in her arm (10:45 am). We monitored blood pressure every 5 minutes, asked the patient to lay on the floor, and fanned her. She refused an ambulance initially, but did ask for one ~30 minutes after vaccine administration. Patient refused an epi-pen.

I woke up on the morning of 2/25, I was having almost double vision in my eyes and I had a really bad headache. I kept asking my husband and son if I looked okay because I just felt really bad. I thought it was maybe a really bad migraine but I had never had a migraine that bad before. I tried to go about my day and drive my son to school By the time I got him to school I was a lot worse. On the way home I got lost coming home because I could not see anything in my left peripheral vision field. Since I got lost, I approached my house from the left. Coming into my driveway from the left meant I could not see so I hit my husbands truck. I had very choppy movements with my legs. I told my husband something was seriously wrong and when he looked at me my entire left side of my face was drooping At that point we went to the hospital. At the hospital I was brought in as a potential stroke I was given a CAT scan and tons of blood works. I was admitted for observation to monitor my heart because my symptoms were so similar to a stroke. An MRI showed that I did in fact have a stroke. I was given atorvastatin 40mg and 80mg aspirin I was in the hospital about a day. At that time a lot of mobility on my left side came back. My peripheral vision came back extremely slow. When I came home I took the week off from work. I followed up with my PCP and neurologist. The neurologist put me on 243mg aspirin and atorvastatin. Since the stroke I've had a really bad headache. I also followed up with a cardiologist who put a heart monito on me for a month. They could not find anything, so I am to follow up with them in 6 months. At this time I am being treated for chronic headaches/migraine. I have noticed that I have weird carpal tunnel symptoms in both hands. I followed up with a hand specialist who informed me that a lot of patients she's seen have had the same issue. I have never had carpal tunnel before so it is strange for me seeing that I have been out of work since February. It is still unknown as to what caused the stroke. I do not have high blood pressure, I did a normal MRI and then an MRV with contrast to make sure that blood flow to my brain was correct. Everything came back normal. The only thing that was different within that month of February was the vaccine. I also am experiencing short term memory loss but I believe it is more of a stroke symptom rather than it being due to the vaccine. I was taken off of my birth control pills while at the hospital and I am still off indefinitely.
LAB_DATA: MRI, CAT scan, MRV, Bloodwork, tested for lupus, MS, clotting factors: Normal

Patient came to Pharmacy today for his J&J vaccine along with his wife who also received her vaccine as well. After I administered the vaccine, the patient got light headed and I asked him if he would like to lay down. I asked if he could hear me after saying his name a few times, no response. I assessed his subjective vitals and could tell he stopped breathing. Called for Pharmacy resident to grab and administer an epi pen. Patient responded within 30 seconds of epi pen administration and started breathing again. Proceeded to call emergency services, first responders arrived within 5 minutes and administered IV fluids and oral ondansetron. Patient left with the ambulance and will follow up tomorrow to make sure everything is ok.

Client received the 1st COVID vaccine Pfizer Lot#EW0185 on 05/22/21 at 3:29 PM. The client presents to the vaccination site today for her 2nd COVID Pfizer vaccine. The following information was obtained with use of a Spanish-English interpreter. The client alerted RN that she "felt like she couldn't breath in a mask" 24 hours after receiving the vaccine while the client was at work. The client states she works in a nursery, where the temperature is usually increased. One RN alerted another RN who responded. The client states she left work, removed her mask, and her symptoms resolved. She states she had eaten and consumed water on the day the symptoms began. The client denied any other signs of anaphylaxis at the time of the initial incident. No medication was administered at the time of the incident. They did not follow up with any medical care providers after developing the symptoms. The client denies any chronic conditions, or current medications. The client has no known allergies. She denies a history of anxiety or shortness of breath while wearing a mask. Vitals obtained by EMT on 06/12/21 at 3:42 were as follows: BP 128/82, HR 62, RR 16. RN submitted a consult to the medical team via text message. Approval was received from PHN via text message. RN provided education regarding s/s of anaphylaxis, to report any symptoms during observation to EMT, to follow up with PCP if the client develops any symptoms post vaccination, when to seek EMS, to consume water prior to vaccination and after, and V-safe. The client was also instructed to wait 30 minutes in the observation period. The client voiced understanding of this. Client received the 2nd COVID vaccine Pfizer Lot#EW0187 on 06/12/21 at approximately 3:55 PM. The client waited in the observation area for 15 minutes and left the premises AMA. The client received the vaccination area without complication and did not alert the EMTs of any symptoms during her observation period.

Perscribed Losartan late December 2020 for hypertension due to problems with HCTZ.  By early January 2021, noted mild persistent tinnitus (previously only very minor and occasional).  I reduced the dose of Loartan from 50mg to 25 mg per day and did note some minor improvement in the tinnitus, as clinic does report ear noise and tinnitus as a side effect from Losartan.   However, the longer I continued Losartan the worse the tinnitus became such that in February it was moderate and in March was severe, such that I discontinued Losartan the day after the 2nd Pfyzer vaccine shot due to the extreme severity of the tinnitus thinking that it was Losartan related.  I am now 2 1/2 months since that last covid vaccine shot and the discontinuation of the Losartan and the tinnitus has gone from 9-10+ (1-10 scale) to 6-8,  but  has not resolved.   My hearing test compared to that of 2 years ago is unchanged and shows minimal hi frequency hearing loss which is inconsequential to any day to day living activities.
LAB_DATA: Hearing test  8/2019 with ENT private practise,  4/2021 Ear doctor where I obtained a consultation for the problem.  MRI of brain and innner ear 3/2021 also normal.   Tapering dose of steroids 6 day in February no effect except to reduce minor eustachian tube dysfunction

SYMPTOM_TEXT: Day 1 of first vaccine - injection site pain, lethargy.  Tachycardia, PVC's, shortness of breath, chest pressure, headache, dizziness, high blood pressure, night sweats, body aches, diarrhea, lethargy began about 4 days post injection.  Felt it was just the initial side effects of vaccine, but it continued.  Feb. 26th - Called MD office for an appt.   Could not get an appt. until March 18th.  March 1st - contacted MD's office via internet and explained symptoms, requested labs and cardiac workup since I could not get an appt.  He ordered labs, stated, "?I don't think checking your cardiac enzymes at this time would be helpful.?  Contacted Health Plan customer service, requested new MD, was told to file a grievance against Dr.  New physician Dr - next appt available was April 13th.   March 4th - With no history of high blood pressure in the past but it continued, began taking my husband's Atenolol daily, 25-50 mg.   Tachycardia, PVC's subside, HTN continues uncontrolled. Contact new physician's office, was told to go to Urgent Care for an EKG.  Did so the next morning with Atenolol on board.  EKG normal, heart rate 60, BP normal.  Told to continue to self medicate with Atenolol.  April 13 - Go to appt with Dr.  He says to continue to take Atenolol, "we are all guinea pigs with the vaccine".  I began to hear about some younger people getting myocarditis and realize that THIS is probably what is going on.
LAB_DATA: Basic labs, EKG, no cardiac enzymes were ordered.
OTHER_MEDS: Prilosec, Glucosamine, Vitamin D, St John's Wort, Fish oil

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 16yo previously healthy male presenting with chest pain. He received second dose of Pfizer Covid vaccine on Wednesday at 3p. That evening, he developed fevers, chills and had trouble sleeping. On Thursday, he began feeling heart palpitations and again slept. Overnight, he developed midline chest pain, and decided to present to the emergency room. His EKG showed elevated ST segments. Labs were remarkable for elevated troponin, leukocytosis, and elevated CRP; echo showed normal function but subtle hypokinesis of the apex. He was given morphine, Tylenol, Ketorolac, 1L NS, and possibly aspirin before being transferred to the ED.   In our ED, he had a reassuring exam, was no longer reporting chest pain. He had labs drawn which showed a white count to 15.3, normal H/H, Plt 152, ESR 12, CRP 10, and Trop T 1.14.   Aside from the above symptoms, he has been in his usual well state without viral symptoms, nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, rash, joint pain, or other symptoms. He has no past medical or surgical history. Immunizations are up to date. His social history is benign.  Patient was admitted to the cardiology floor for continued monitoring of his troponin levels and EKG. An echocardiogram was performed which showed mild LV systolic dysfunction. He was then treated with IVIG 2g/kg and started on methylprednisolone IV q12h. He remained asymptomatic with no chest pain throughout his admission. He was transitioned over to PO steroids on 6/13 which he tolerated well. On day of discharge, his troponin levels were trending down. Cardiac MRI showed an area of late gadolinium enhancement in the LV, with no abnormal function.   By time of discharge, patient was well-appearing, vitals stable, demonstrating good PO intake including tolerance of PO steroid. Prescriptions sent to preferred pharmacy. Follow up with cardiology to be arranged. Discharge instructions and return precautions reviewed with patient and parent, who expressed good understanding and agreement with plan.  Reasons for new, changed, and discontinued medications:  - Prednisone  - Famotidine Patient was admitted for management of myocarditis thought to be due to his SARS-CoV2 vaccination. He received IVIG and steroids. He had multiple EKGs, echocardiogram, and a cardiac MRI. He showed improvement during his hospitalization. He will be followed closely by Cardiology who will advise return to exercise and repeat imaging needs.  **Please note that we do not have access to the vaccination records (lot, etc)**

After receiving a second Pfizer COVID-19 vaccine on 5/20/21, Patient began to experience the sudden onset of a severe headache, along with other stroke-like symptoms: dizziness, numbness/weakness of left face, hand, and leg, and confusion. (Following the first dose of the Pfizer COVID-19 on/about 4/23/21, she also experienced the sudden onset of a severe headache and dizziness, which eventually subsided.)-  On 5/22/21, patient went to the Emergency Department. The ER physician did a quick neurological examination, observed some concerning symptoms, and ordered a CAT scan of the head without contrast. The CT scan showed that patient had suffered a subdural hematoma (bleeding between the skull and brain). The CT scan showed evidence of both subacute and acute bleeding, causing serious pressure on the brain, and acute bleeding, predominantly on the right side, but also on the left side. She was admitted to the hospital, and underwent some blood tests and a follow-up CAT scan of the head without contrast. Since the CT scan indicated that bleeding was still present and causing serious symptoms, she underwent an embolization procedure performed by a neurosurgeon to curtail the bleeding. She remained under observation until she was discharged on 6/3/21. Patient was fine and healthy until she received the Pfizer COVID-19 vaccines.
LAB_DATA: CAT scans of the head without contrast, showed subdural hematoma

I got really worried about the rash and my husband took me to ER at hospital March 11, 2021. They did a lot of bloodwork. They gave me a shot of Prednisone and Benadryl. They prescribed those to me as well and sent me on my way. Benadryl helped. It made the rash go away but it took awhile. It was splotchy rashes all over - the dermatologist said my skin was inflamed everywhere. After it started to go away, my skin peeled like it was a sunburn. It was not itchy at all - just turned splotchy red and then peeled. My primary care doctor recommended further. I went to an allergist, Cardiologist - because I do have some heart issues; and also a pulmonologist to check me out. I am still experiencing joint pain to this day - and especially in my feet that I never had before. So I have an arthritis doctor to see what is going on.

Patient is a healthy 15 year old male presenting with chest pain in the setting of recent SARS-CoV2 vaccination. He was in his usual state of health until he received the second dose of the Pfizer/BNT SARS-CoV2 vaccination on Thursday 6/10. Shortly after and into the following day, he developed fatigue, chills, and a headache, which resolved within 24 hours. However, early this morning at around 2am, he awoke with sharp central chest pain associated with some shortness of breath, radiating to his left, prompting him to present to the ED.  Initially presented to Hospital ED. Vitals stable. Labs notable for troponin 0.07 and d-dimer 1.48. EKG with sinus rhythm, ST elevation in inferior leads. Given ibuprofen 600mg and contacted Cardiology, who recommended transfer to another ED for echocardiogram and further evaluation.  Here in the ED, vital stable, exam non-focal. Labs notable for troponin 0.13 and CRP 3.0; CBC, chem 10, LFTs, BNP, all within normal limits. CXR normal. Echo done which showed normal function (prelim read). Seen by ID who recommended standard workup for vaccine-induced myocarditis. He was admitted to the floor in stable condition.  Hospital Course: Due to rising troponin during hospital day 1 (peak 0.23), patient was treated with IVIG 2 g/kg (6/14) and methylprednisone 30 mg BID (6/14 - 6/15). On 6/15 a cardiac MRI was obtained that showed a small area of late gadolinium enhancement of the LV with normal function.  Troponin was trended every 12 hours and had decreased to 0.11 on 6/15 AM. He was transitioned to oral prednisone 30 mg BID to complete a total steroid course of 5 days (6/14 - 6/18). During admission he was found to be EBV PCR positive with all other viral testing including EBV serologies pending. It is still thought this is likely due to post-vaccine inflammation and not viral myocarditis but serologies should be followed up as outpatient.   By time of discharge, patient was well-appearing, vitals stable, demonstrating good PO intake. Prescriptions sent to preferred pharmacy. Follow up with cardiology. Discharge instructions and return precautions reviewed with patient and parent, who expressed good understanding and agreement with plan.   Reasons for new, changed, and discontinued medications:  Prednisone for myocarditis  Famotidine for stomach protection while on prednisone  Discharged home with follow up tests scheduled for 6/17/21.
LAB_DATA: Relevant Diagnostic Images/Studies:  Cardiac MRI (6/15): ? Normal biventricular size and systolic function. No regional wall motion abnormalities. ? Small focal area of left ventricular late gadolinium enhancement consistent with myocarditis. ? No significant valvular dysfunction. ? No pericardial effusion.  Echo (6/13): ? Mild tricuspid regurgitation. ? No other significant valvar dysfunction. ? No significant right ventricular hypertension. ? Normal left ventricular size and systolic function. ? Qualitatively normal right ventricular systolic function. ? No pericardial effusion. ? Incomplete anatomic survey.   CXR (6/13): Lungs: Clear.  Heart/mediastinum: The cardiomediastinal silhouette is normal in size with normal contours.  Pleural effusion: None.  Pneumothorax: None.  Osseous/soft tissue structures: Normal.  Included upper abdomen: Normal. SYMPTOM_TEXT: Started the day great and went and got the 2nd dose of Moderna on 6/12/21 at 940am. I felt fine throughout the day and I started getting a little dizzy and disoriented around 5pm  and as it was explained to me it would be expected to get side effects. Later in the evening around 8pm I started to get extremely dizzy, tired, and having a low grade fever of 100.5F. I Later developed a headache and I had to go lie down for the rest of the night. As I was sleeping throughout the night and waking up multiple times shivering and being extremely cold, I was taking my temperature throughout the night and It would be climbing up from 100.5F and it reached 103.7F. At that point I wanted to get up and take some fever reducer medicines but I was unable to get out of the bed as I was very dizzy and disoriented and I was having extreme muscle and joint pains that I wasnt unable to move at all. I needed to go to the restroom and get a drink and I was unable to do that.  I had considered going to the ER but I waited it out and wouldnt go unless my temperature kept rising. I eventually tried going to the bathroom but at that point I had passed out and woke up in the morning between my bedroom and bathroom. On sunday 6/13 I was continuing to have symptoms and felt extremely ill throughout the day.  I woke up and the fever had gone away but I still had the symptoms mentioned above and also had ringing in my ears. Throughout the day I was trying to do stuff around the house but I was unable to do that and go to work. I would randomly pass out at times either on my desk or just sitting on the couch. That was throughout sunday then on monday I was feeling a lot better almost all symptoms had gone away but I was still a bit dizzy and had body aches and was unable to go to work and do basic stuff around the house. Tuesday I was mostly feeling fine but still felt a bit dizzy and disoriented and extremely fatigued but I was able to go to work. Wednesday I am feeling almost 100% normal but I do get dizzy at times and I am still extremely fatigued.
LAB_DATA: Covid self test- Negative starting from Sunday until Wednesday.
OTHER_MEDS: Levothyroxine, Omeprazole, Metformin, Folic Acid, Vit B complex, Vit D3
HISTORY: Under active thyroid, diabetes type 2, anemia,

Lasted for 4 days that way.  I still feel like I am constantly winded and I as of today have only regained about half the lung capacity I had prior to incident, and that is just over 1 month mark. I also now have been getting these bad facial breakouts particularly on and around my nose and forehead /;eyes area. I never ever had any acne issues to speak of prior, even as a teen and during puberty. Never had any acne ever and now its bad breakouts some appear to may even leave ling term scarring in certain spots. My day to day diet and normal habits have not been added to or altered in any way either. My heart feels like it beats twice as fast and twice as hard now and I am always short of breath now too. I do not have a family doctor to go and see and I was afraid to call for an e.m.t. or go to the e.r. at the early onset of it all. I truly hought I was a gonner a couple of times though throughout the first 4 days.
HISTORY: None.  Normally a fit, active, fast paced, healthy go getter type.

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 3 days after I received a first doze of Pfizer vaccine on May 13, I found out that I was pregnant, about 5 weeks. I consulted with my OBGYN and also called CDC phone number to consult regarding getting the 2nd doze, and both encouraged me to get the 2nd doze. My bloodwork showed low levels of progestrerone, so I was prescribed it to support the pregnancy.  My 2nd doze was on June 3, and on the next day after the vaccination I've experienced strong vatigue, headache, and overall low-grade fever achy sensations.  On the 4th day after getting vaccinated with my 2nd doze, I got a terrible migrain that lasted for 48 hours; I was unable to keep any food or fluids in, and actually lost 7.5 lbs over the period of 2 days. A couple of days after that, I had a similar migraine that lasted by 24 hours, and I lost another 3 lbs.   Today, June 16, I came in for my 1st 10-week sonogram, only to find out that I had a Blighted Ovum Miscarriage. This is make it my 3rd pregnancy and my 3rd miscarrige. My OBGYN has ordered some blood tests, and we're trying to get as much information about the possible cause on our end.  In the meantime, I felt obligated to share my story in case the vaccine had any hand in this...  I get the flu shot every year, and I am pro vaccination. I've been tested negative for COVID-19; prior to getting teh vcaccine I also checked for anti-bodies, and the result was negative as well.

Patient fainted for less than 10 seconds, as I cautiously helped lay him down on the floor. I checked for vitals, and elevated patient's legs, and gave him ice to help. Patient remained in laying position for 15 minutes, regained strength and sat up for another 15 minutes, in which time, he was given water to drink and a protein bar to eat.
